icies >> Logon/Logoff >> \"Audit Account Lockout\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nLogon/Logoff >> Account Lockout - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAccount Lockout events can be used to identify potentially malicious logon attempts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-71759","SV-86383","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"7836","uuid":"face19a0-dcc2-4ad0-abfe-72a83a0a7917","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 74BF5604BF3B67B919F97D1CC7D3137DBF3187B4\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to audit Logon/Logoff - Account Lockout failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220756","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220756","title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220756","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214","rule_id_src":"SV-220756r991578_rule","rule_id":"SV-220756","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000060","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Logon/Logoff - Group Membership successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Logon/Logoff >> \"Audit Group Membership\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following.  If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nLogon/Logoff >> Group Membership - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Group Membership records information related to the group membership of a user's logon token.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-77947","V-63457","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"2874","uuid":"3d9cfd3f-54e5-4df5-bac2-dfd01992a055","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220757","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220757","title":"SRG-OS-000032-GPOS-00013","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220757","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000032-GPOS-00013","rule_id_src":"SV-220757r958406_rule","rule_id":"SV-220757","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000065","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Logon/Logoff - Logoff successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Logon/Logoff >> \"Audit Logoff\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following.  If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nLogon/Logoff >> Logoff - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nLogoff records user logoffs. If this is an interactive logoff, it is recorded on the local system. If it is to a network share, it is recorded on the system accessed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63459","SV-77951","CCI-000067","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"5989","uuid":"de9649e1-9f17-4b74-83e0-c6564553addb","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9E85E5D0E3D7EC161B3BBF9DEC249FE23A6425C9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to audit Logon/Logoff - Logoff successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220758","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220758","title":"SRG-OS-000032-GPOS-00013","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220758","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000032-GPOS-00013","rule_id_src":"SV-220758r958406_rule","rule_id":"SV-220758","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000070","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Logon/Logoff - Logon failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Logon/Logoff >> \"Audit Logon\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"1