s (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following.  If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nLogon/Logoff >> Special Logon - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSpecial Logon records special logons which have administrative privileges and can be used to elevate processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63469","SV-77959","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"6924","uuid":"4bb38e83-62da-40d4-b484-64a0223ad6d8","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4AEB27DD9ABF45F24BD47A4AE4CA15689C3795B5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to audit Logon/Logoff - Special Logon successes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220761","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220761","title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220761","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","rule_id_src":"SV-220761r991583_rule","rule_id":