heck_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fAllowToGetHelp\n \nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote assistance allows another user to view or take control of the local session of a user.  Solicited assistance is help that is specifically requested by the local user.  This may allow unauthorized parties access to the resources on the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78141","V-63651","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"1102","uuid":"f26b112d-f38d-44e0-b194-3822f14982df","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FB8504D4B2C1E27E7366DA8F7F46084027557DA8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Solicited Remote Assistance must not be allowed.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220824","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220824","title":"SRG-OS-000379-GPOS-00164","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220824","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000379-GPOS-00164","rule_id_src":"SV-220824r971545_rule","rule_id":"SV-220824","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000165","rule_title":"Unauthenticated RPC clients must be restricted from connecting to the RPC server.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Remote Procedure Call >> \"Restrict Unauthenticated RPC clients\" to \"Enabled\" and \"Authenticated\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Rpc\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictRemoteClients\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring RPC to restrict unauthenticated RPC clients from connecting to the RPC server will prevent anonymous connections.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63657","SV-78147","CCI-001967"],"reference_identifier":"9230","uuid":"ebe64e6b-1c5c-4d23-998c-5dbe0ae8901a","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 47623FFFA3A93CED0DCDF4A96129E7E4BB40AEE5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthenticated RPC clients must be restricted from connecting to the RPC server.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220825","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220825","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220825","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220825r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220825","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000170","rule_title":"The setting to allow Microsoft accounts to be optional for modern style apps must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> App Runtime >> \"Allow Microsoft accounts to be optional\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows 10 LTSC\\B versions do not support the Microsoft Store and modern apps; this is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: MSAOptional\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Control of credentials and the system must be maintained within the enterprise.  Enabling this setting allows enterprise credentials to be used with modern style apps that support this, instead of Microsoft accounts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63659","SV-78149","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1195","uuid":"ae2db5a0-d8bb-42e6-a990-c40d8a9504ce","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1D47A0B2CB40D869F3379A29E3573DAAC0DB65EF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The setting to allow Microsoft accounts to be optional for modern style apps must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220826","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220826","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220826","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220826r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220826","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000175","rule_title":"The Application Compatibility Program Inventory must be prevented from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Application Compatibility >> \"Turn off Inventory Collector\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppCompat\\\n\nValue Name: DisableInventory\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  This setting will prevent the Program Inventory from collecting data about a system and sending the information to Microsoft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63663","SV-78153","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8912","uuid":"0a13908d-1c4e-4b9c-b514-9ca4e4455c0a","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2FB1C9356B89717DBFF7C81BA2E609868A6DB6D4\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Application Compatibility Program Inventory must be prevented from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220827","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220827","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220827","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-220827r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-220827","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000180","rule_title":"Autoplay must be turned off for non-volume devices.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> \"Disallow Autoplay for non-volume devices\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoAutoplayfornonVolume\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing autoplay to execute may introduce malicious code to a system.  Autoplay begins reading from a drive as soon as you insert media in the drive.  As a result, the setup file of programs or music on audio media may start.  This setting will disable autoplay for non-volume devices (such as Media Transfer Protocol (MTP) devices).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78157","V-63667","CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"3098","uuid":"baadffa7-9322-4af4-b3eb-e5481640b081","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DC803887BB8CC49DE6C6168ED523CB1F10B75D81\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Autoplay must be turned off for non-volume devices.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220828","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220828","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220828","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-220828r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-220828","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000185","rule_title":"The default autorun behavior must be configured to prevent autorun commands.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> \"Set the default behavior for AutoRun\" to \"Enabled:Do not execute any autorun commands\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoAutorun\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing autorun commands to execute may introduce malicious code to a system.  Configuring this setting prevents autorun commands from executing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63671","SV-78161","CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"8864","uuid":"291452e7-e635-43e1-b2d7-48fbd4c9c288","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 911A479F1247F591BD73A655F72C5AF0346897EC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The default autorun behavior must be configured to prevent autorun commands.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220829","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220829","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220829","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-220829r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-220829","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000190","rule_title":"Autoplay must be disabled for all drives.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> \"Turn off AutoPlay\" to \"Enabled:All Drives\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDriveTypeAutoRun\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x000000ff (255)\n\nNote: If the value for NoDriveTypeAutorun is entered manually, it must be entered as \"ff\" when Hexadecimal is selected, or \"255\" with Decimal selected.  Using the policy value specified in the Fix section will enter it correctly.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing autoplay to execute may introduce malicious code to a system.  Autoplay begins reading from a drive as soon as you insert media in the drive.  As a result, the setup file of programs or music on audio media may start.  By default, autoplay is disabled on removable drives, such as the floppy disk drive (but not the CD-ROM drive) and on network drives.  If you enable this policy, you can also disable autoplay on all drives.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63673","SV-78163","CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"5150","uuid":"32550739-8874-4d52-ae02-a4ff58721721","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A8835A364B79D6F0CD5C64AC274794E3C457BA38\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Autoplay must be disabled for all drives.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220830","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220830","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220830","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220830r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220830","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000195","rule_title":"Enhanced anti-spoofing for facial recognition must be enabled on Window 10.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Biometrics >> Facial Features >> \"Configure enhanced anti-spoofing\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nv1607:\nThe policy name is \"Use enhanced anti-spoofing when available\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows 10 v1507 LTSB version does not include this setting; it is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Biometrics\\FacialFeatures\\\n\nValue Name: EnhancedAntiSpoofing\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enhanced anti-spoofing provides additional protections when using facial recognition with devices that support it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78167","V-63677","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1298","uuid":"b19b1527-fade-4046-883e-39688e1c4030","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8D5910DE7471A345118420E81222B67F4CABED9B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Enhanced anti-spoofing for facial recognition must be enabled on Window 10.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220831","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220831","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220831","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220831r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220831","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000197","rule_title":"Microsoft consumer experiences must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Cloud Content >> \"Turn off Microsoft consumer experiences\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows 10 v1507 LTSB version does not include this setting; it is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CloudContent\\\n\nValue Name: DisableWindowsConsumerFeatures\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft consumer experiences provides suggestions and notifications to users, which may include the installation of Windows Store apps.  Organizations may control the execution of applications through other means such as whitelisting.  Turning off Microsoft consumer experiences will help prevent the unwanted installation of suggested applications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-71771","SV-86395","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6243","uuid":"965c2f99-bd14-4bfb-a3a6-8ad0b92ddb85","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220832","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220832","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220832","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-220832r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-220832","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000200","rule_title":"Administrator accounts must not be enumerated during elevation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Credential User Interface >> \"Enumerate administrator accounts on elevation\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\CredUI\\\n\nValue Name: EnumerateAdministrators\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enumeration of administrator accounts when elevating can provide part of the logon information to an unauthorized user.  This setting configures the system to always require users to type in a username and password to elevate a running application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63679","SV-78169","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"7971","uuid":"4f7ea3ba-5c97-4084-81f0-9e488434609e","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DE22880CB521E1700E30B6724D218C2C0335B36F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Administrator accounts must not be enumerated during elevation.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220833","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220833","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220833","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220833r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220833","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000204","rule_title":"If Enhanced diagnostic data is enabled it must be limited to the minimum required to support Windows Analytics.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Data Collection and Preview Builds >> \"Limit Enhanced diagnostic data to the minimum required by Windows Analytics\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Enable Windows Analytics collection\" selected in \"Options:\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting requires v1709 or later of Windows 10; it is NA for prior versions.\n\nIf \"Enhanced\" level is enabled for telemetry, this must be configured. If \"Security\" or \"Basic\" are configured, this is NA. (See V-220834).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DataCollection\\\n\nValue Name: LimitEnhancedDiagnosticDataWindowsAnalytics\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Limiting this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise. The \"Enhanced\" level for telemetry includes additional information beyond \"Security\" and \"Basic\" on how Windows and apps are used and advanced reliability data. Windows Analytics can use a \"limited enhanced\" level to provide information such as health data for devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-96859","V-82145","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3105","uuid":"d937a0aa-4078-4ada-8d39-4732fa51048a","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 061F47875C57AB63334C587F995862C50413FF01\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'If Enhanced diagnostic data is enabled it must be limited to the minimum required to support Windows Analytics.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220834","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220834","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220834","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220834r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220834","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000205","rule_title":"Windows Telemetry must not be configured to Full.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Data Collection and Preview Builds >> \"Allow Telemetry\" to \"Enabled\" with \"0 - Security [Enterprise Only]\" or \"1 - Basic\" selected in \"Options:\". \n\nIf an organization is using v1709 or later of Windows 10, this may be configured to \"2 - Enhanced\" to support Windows Analytics. V-220833 must also be configured to limit the Enhanced diagnostic data to the minimum required by Windows Analytics.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DataCollection\\\n\nValue Name: AllowTelemetry\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (Security)\n0x00000001 (1) (Basic)\n\nIf an organization is using v1709 or later of Windows 10, this may be configured to \"Enhanced\" to support Windows Analytics. V-220833 must also be configured to limit the Enhanced diagnostic data to the minimum required by Windows Analytics. This registry value will then be 0x00000002 (2).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Limiting this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise. The \"Security\" option for Telemetry configures the lowest amount of data, effectively none outside of the Malicious Software Removal Tool (MSRT), Defender, and telemetry client settings. \"Basic\" sends basic diagnostic and usage data and may be required to support some Microsoft services. \"Enhanced\" includes additional information on how Windows and apps are used and advanced reliability data. Windows Analytics can use a \"limited enhanced\" level to provide information such as health data for devices. This requires the configuration of an additional setting available with v1709 and later of Windows 10.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63683","SV-78173","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8499","uuid":"0c4fbeb5-d195-4438-a129-3650c0c6bb18","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 32FA0BD5B99B22170752E09789B7BC59CA18DF81\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Telemetry must not be configured to Full.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220835","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220835","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220835","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220835r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220835","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000206","rule_title":"Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the internet.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Delivery Optimization >> \"Download Mode\" to \"Enabled\" with any option except \"Internet\" selected.\n\nAcceptable selections include:\nBypass (100)\nGroup (2)\nHTTP only (0)\nLAN (1)\nSimple (99)\n\nv1507 (LTSB) does not include this group policy setting locally. For domain-joined systems, configure through domain group policy as \"HTTP only (0)\" or \"Lan (1)\". \n\nFor standalone or nondomain-joined systems, configure using Settings >> Update & Security >> Windows Update >> Advanced Options >> \"Choose how updates are delivered\" with either \"Off\" or \"PCs on my local network\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeliveryOptimization\\\n\nValue Name: DODownloadMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) - No peering (HTTP Only)\n0x00000001 (1) - Peers on same NAT only (LAN)\n0x00000002 (2) - Local Network / Private group peering (Group)\n0x00000063 (99) - Simple download mode, no peering (Simple)\n0x00000064 (100) - Bypass mode, Delivery Optimization not used (Bypass)\n\nA value of 0x00000003 (3), Internet, is a finding.\n\nv1507 LTSB:\nDomain joined systems:\nVerify the registry value above.\nIf the value is not 0x00000000 (0) or 0x00000001 (1), this is a finding.\n\nStandalone or nondomain-joined systems (configured in Settings):\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\DeliveryOptimization\\Config\\\n\nValue Name: DODownloadMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) - Off\n0x00000001 (1) - LAN","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows 10 allows Windows Update to obtain updates from additional sources instead of Microsoft. In addition to Microsoft, updates can be obtained from and sent to PCs on the local network as well as on the internet. This is part of the Windows Update trusted process; however, to minimize outside exposure, obtaining updates from or sending to systems on the internet must be prevented.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-80171","V-65681","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8697","uuid":"29c5e6fa-2edc-4f9b-b9a1-40ac99d9ca38","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8DB999E2B016A2239514709F5771151784E2E8EC\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the internet.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220836","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220836","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220836","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220836r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220836","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000210","rule_title":"The Windows Defender SmartScreen for Explorer must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Configure Windows Defender SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Warn and prevent bypass\" selected. \n\nWindows 10 includes duplicate policies for this setting. It can also be configured under Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender SmartScreen >> Explorer.\n\nv1607 LTSB:\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Configure Windows SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\". (Selection options are not available.)\n\nv1507 LTSB:\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Configure Windows SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Require approval from an administrator before running downloaded unknown software\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSmartScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nAnd\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ShellSmartScreenLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: Block\n\nv1607 LTSB:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSmartScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nv1507 LTSB:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSmartScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows Defender SmartScreen helps protect systems from programs downloaded from the internet that may be malicious. Enabling Windows Defender SmartScreen will warn or prevent users from running potentially malicious programs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63685","SV-78175","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2616","uuid":"b90f4a26-b010-463d-b7e7-2b367b97ecfb","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A84CD69B969B87D4796F5740E073272DF477A4F3\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Windows Defender SmartScreen for Explorer must be enabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220837","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220837","title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220837","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","rule_id_src":"SV-220837r958928_rule","rule_id":"SV-220837","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000215","rule_title":"Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for data execution prevention to be turned on for file explorer.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Turn off Data Execution Prevention for Explorer\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for data execution prevention to be turned on for file explorer.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDataExecutionPrevention\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Data Execution Prevention (DEP) provides additional protection by performing  checks on memory to help prevent malicious code from running.  This setting will prevent Data Execution Prevention from being turned off for File Explorer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63689","SV-78179","CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"1788","uuid":"7f73f46b-03fb-4584-a75e-4840abdddbc1","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EB3E7F2F9E437460B3D39DDA276694C9588A7C08\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220838","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220838","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220838","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-220838r958902_rule","rule_id":"SV-220838","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000220","rule_title":"Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be enabled.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Turn off heap termination on corruption\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be enabled.\n\nIf the registry Value Name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoHeapTerminationOnCorruption\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Legacy plug-in applications may continue to function when a File Explorer session has become corrupt.  Disabling this feature will prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78181","V-63691","CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"6929","uuid":"85858a1d-a65b-43d6-9353-2a0299f56364","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EA3437BC9468D3596899B050C07AF2161A5BAAF2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220839","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220839","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220839","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220839r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220839","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000225","rule_title":"File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for file explorer.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Turn off shell protocol protected mode\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for file explorer.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: PreXPSP2ShellProtocolBehavior\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The shell protocol will  limit the set of folders applications can open when run in protected mode.  Restricting files an application can open, to a limited set of folders, increases the security of Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78185","V-63695","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5939","uuid":"fb2af62d-674a-4674-9631-811ecb116974","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 02FF549E9572EBBB8FF6946841641D3F4995A58E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220840","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220840","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220840","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220840r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220840","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000230","rule_title":"Users must not be allowed to ignore Windows Defender SmartScreen filter warnings for malicious websites in Microsoft Edge.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Edge >> \"Prevent bypassing Windows Defender SmartScreen prompts for sites\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nWindows 10 includes duplicate policies for this setting. It can also be configured under Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender SmartScreen >> Microsoft Edge.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nWindows 10 LTSC\\B versions do not include Microsoft Edge, this is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftEdge\\PhishingFilter\\\n\nValue Name: PreventOverride\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows Defender SmartScreen filter in Microsoft Edge provides warning messages and blocks potentially malicious websites and file downloads.  If users are allowed to ignore warnings from the Windows Defender SmartScreen filter they could still access malicious websites.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63699","SV-78189","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4890","uuid":"aebb6b50-e5b9-4756-afc7-878a71fe8e75","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C6A0188F30F59DB6B8F3F4053905667F59BBF250\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Users must not be allowed to ignore Windows Defender SmartScreen filter warnings for malicious websites in Microsoft Edge.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220841","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220841","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220841","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220841r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220841","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000235","rule_title":"Users must not be allowed to ignore Windows Defender SmartScreen filter warnings for unverified files in Microsoft Edge.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Edge >> \"Prevent bypassing Windows Defender SmartScreen prompts for files\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nWindows 10 includes duplicate policies for this setting. It can also be configured under Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender SmartScreen >> Microsoft Edge.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nWindows 10 LTSC\\B versions do not include Microsoft Edge, this is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftEdge\\PhishingFilter\\\n\nValue Name: PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows Defender SmartScreen filter in Microsoft Edge provides warning messages and blocks potentially malicious websites and file downloads.  If users are allowed to ignore warnings from the Windows Defender SmartScreen filter they could still download potentially malicious files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78191","V-63701","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2097","uuid":"27f05f27-b701-47d4-b8b6-209548a7be48","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 29011BEBA30A0ED43D703225681E634BDC1E9D28\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Users must not be allowed to ignore Windows Defender SmartScreen filter warnings for unverified files in Microsoft Edge.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220842","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220842","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220842","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220842r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220842","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000238","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to prevent certificate error overrides in Microsoft Edge.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Edge >> \"Prevent certificate error overrides\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1809 of Windows 10; it is NA for prior versions.\n\nWindows 10 LTSC\\B versions do not include Microsoft Edge; this is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftEdge\\Internet Settings\\\n\nValue Name: PreventCertErrorOverrides\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Web security certificates provide an indication whether a site is legitimate. This policy setting prevents the user from ignoring Secure Sockets Layer/Transport Layer Security (SSL/TLS) certificate errors that interrupt browsing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-96853","V-82139","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8415","uuid":"43f10e51-e700-4e69-a2d9-b70541cbd8fb","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B9A03D7AA262BB84F6FDC636D98F8248FDDF7A70\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to prevent certificate error overrides in Microsoft Edge.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220843","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220843","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220843","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220843r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220843","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000245","rule_title":"The password manager function in the Edge browser must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Edge >> \"Configure Password Manager\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows 10 LTSC\\B versions do not include Microsoft Edge, this is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftEdge\\Main\\\n\nValue Name: FormSuggest Passwords\n\nType: REG_SZ\nValue: no","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Passwords save locally for re-use when browsing may be subject to compromise.  Disabling the Edge password manager will prevent this for the browser.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63709","SV-78199","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4562","uuid":"2509c9ef-7d4c-43c3-8e19-3183e723029b","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4677E3E3435AC0EE4FC62642165F0A726C186E1B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The password manager function in the Edge browser must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220844","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220844","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220844","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220844r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220844","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000250","rule_title":"The Windows Defender SmartScreen filter for Microsoft Edge must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Edge >> \"Configure Windows Defender SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nWindows 10 includes duplicate policies for this setting. It can also be configured under Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender SmartScreen >> Microsoft Edge.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nWindows 10 LTSC\\B versions do not include Microsoft Edge, this is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftEdge\\PhishingFilter\\\n\nValue Name: EnabledV9\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows Defender SmartScreen filter in Microsoft Edge provides warning messages and blocks potentially malicious websites.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78203","V-63713","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1869","uuid":"393777f7-7813-4f94-bb4b-c4f2ce5f2f58","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C1556E65BE7C20C86A9FC766E332A78D392AAEBF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Defender SmartScreen filter for Microsoft Edge must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220845","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220845","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220845","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220845r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220845","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000252","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to disable Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting >> \"Enables or disables Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA for Windows 10 LTSC\\B versions 1507 and 1607.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\GameDVR\\\n\nValue Name: AllowGameDVR\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting is intended for use with games, however it could potentially record screen shots of other applications and expose sensitive data.  Disabling the feature will prevent this from occurring.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89091","V-74417","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5854","uuid":"f476d62b-6056-44e5-b3db-6c8598441e7c","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0765240E58A5E7D0005D7914CCDEE29D735849D2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to disable Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220846","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220846","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220846","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220846r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220846","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000255","rule_title":"The use of a hardware security device with Windows Hello for Business must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Hello for Business >> \"Use a hardware security device\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nv1507 LTSB:\nThe policy path is Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Passport for Work.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Virtual desktop implementations currently may not support the use of TPMs. For virtual desktop implementations where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\PassportForWork\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecurityDevice\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The use of a Trusted Platform Module (TPM) to store keys for Windows Hello for Business provides additional security.  Keys stored in the TPM may only be used on that system while keys stored using software are more susceptible to compromise and could be used on other systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78207","V-63717","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9839","uuid":"f67958d4-a0a6-4cdf-964c-67a597146b2c","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DA69971A9E03923D43B3D044B7DE23F5B0D7C3C4\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The use of a hardware security device with Windows Hello for Business must be enabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220847","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220847","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220847","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220847r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220847","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000260","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to require a minimum pin length of six characters or greater.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> PIN Complexity >> \"Minimum PIN length\" to \"6\" or greater. \n\nv1607 LTSB:\nThe policy path is Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Hello for Business >> Pin Complexity.\n\nv1507 LTSB:\nThe policy path is Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Passport for Work >> Pin Complexity.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\PassportForWork\\PINComplexity\\\n\nValue Name:  MinimumPINLength\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  6 (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows allows the use of PINs as well as biometrics for authentication without sending a password to a network or website where it could be compromised.  Longer minimum PIN lengths increase the available combinations an attacker would have to attempt.  Shorter minimum length significantly reduces the strength.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78211","V-63721","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5227","uuid":"0a19e8db-b02e-4d6b-ac2d-ebf731c4f91b","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5594A857BC67B85BBFE069117BA2CDA1F0939538\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows 10 must be configured to require a minimum pin length of six characters or greater.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220848","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220848","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220848","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-220848r1051029_rule","rule_id":"SV-220848","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000270","rule_title":"Passwords must not be saved in the Remote Desktop Client.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Connection Client >> \"Do not allow passwords to be saved\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordSaving\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client could allow an unauthorized user to establish a remote desktop session to another system. The system must be configured to prevent users from saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63729","SV-78219","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"9992","uuid":"8b1fc258-6193-4a44-ade0-cddd13d648bb","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A5DDC79DC6A9D54AC9B89EF33C45E64838C440B7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Passwords must not be saved in the Remote Desktop Client.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220849","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220849","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220849","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-220849r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-220849","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000275","rule_title":"Local drives must be prevented from sharing with Remote Desktop Session Hosts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Device and Resource Redirection >> \"Do not allow drive redirection\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fDisableCdm\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preventing users from sharing the local drives on their client computers to Remote Session Hosts that they access helps reduce possible exposure of sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78221","V-63731","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"1807","uuid":"1ac318d1-1ff1-4f18-a5b8-632bb712fe1b","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BA6F196198C1CA2A6F4DD63AF557E1DA59F9C432\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Local drives must be prevented from sharing with Remote Desktop Session Hosts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220850","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220850","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220850","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-220850r1051030_rule","rule_id":"SV-220850","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000280","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security >> \"Always prompt for password upon connection\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fPromptForPassword\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the ability of users to supply passwords automatically as part of their remote desktop connection. Disabling this setting would allow anyone to use the stored credentials in a connection item to connect to the terminal server.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78223","V-63733","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"8247","uuid":"c1f942ce-14a1-4d9a-b66b-a95866482116","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EA5E136035F829E2016D3302FF1A357476CF61A7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220851","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220851","title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220851","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","rule_id_src":"SV-220851r991554_rule","rule_id":"SV-220851","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000285","rule_title":"The Remote Desktop Session Host must require secure RPC communications.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security \"Require secure RPC communication\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fEncryptRPCTraffic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing unsecure RPC communication exposes the system to man in the middle attacks and data disclosure attacks. A man in the middle attack occurs when an intruder captures packets between a client and server and modifies them before allowing the packets to be exchanged. Usually the attacker will modify the information in the packets in an attempt to cause either the client or server to reveal sensitive information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63737","SV-78227","CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"5971","uuid":"3fb5bfcc-b215-474e-8c77-5656d9e7a000","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220852","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220852","title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220852","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","rule_id_src":"SV-220852r958408_rule","rule_id":"SV-220852","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000290","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to the required level.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security >> \"Set client connection encryption level\" to \"Enabled\" and \"High Level\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: MinEncryptionLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote connections must be encrypted to prevent interception of data or sensitive information. Selecting \"High Level\" will ensure encryption of Remote Desktop Services sessions in both directions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63741","SV-78231","CCI-000068","CCI-002890"],"reference_identifier":"4594","uuid":"83441201-9a31-4944-a556-d1fefaa25a4b","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 379A36B7E1332E91E486D79FB7E43286D1F79FBB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to the required level.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220853","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220853","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220853","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220853r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220853","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000295","rule_title":"Attachments must be prevented from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> RSS Feeds >> \"Prevent downloading of enclosures\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: DisableEnclosureDownload\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attachments from RSS feeds may not be secure.  This setting will prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78233","V-63743","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5225","uuid":"c1f38431-5767-45df-86f1-98190345de92","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 559D2D4AFF49AB3F7794611DDBD964C153BFFC58\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Attachments must be prevented from being downloaded from RSS feeds.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220854","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220854","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220854","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220854r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220854","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000300","rule_title":"Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP must not be used.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for the Windows RSS platform to not use Basic authentication over HTTP connections.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> RSS Feeds >> \"Turn on Basic feed authentication over HTTP\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for the Windows RSS platform to not use Basic authentication over HTTP connections.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasicAuthInClear\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain text passwords that could be used to compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78237","V-63747","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3891","uuid":"b1e78e52-f33c-4343-99b0-86ee663ed8f7","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5BE09AC10FBB271EE0A9869AAAE223A2DE483E90\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP must not be used.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220855","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220855","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220855","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220855r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220855","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000305","rule_title":"Indexing of encrypted files must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Search >> \"Allow indexing of encrypted files\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Windows Search\\\n\nValue Name: AllowIndexingEncryptedStoresOrItems\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Indexing of encrypted files may expose sensitive data.  This setting prevents encrypted files from being indexed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63751","SV-78241","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5191","uuid":"66fe5a99-922b-43a6-b0cd-86f6d86d28f2","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AAA924583D6187F28A77D8F56823E10B54680D7F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Indexing of encrypted files must be turned off.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220856","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220856","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220856","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-220856r1051031_rule","rule_id":"SV-220856","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000310","rule_title":"Users must be prevented from changing installation options.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> \"Allow user control over installs\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: EnableUserControl\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Installation options for applications are typically controlled by administrators. This setting prevents users from changing installation options that may bypass security features.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63321","SV-77811","CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"9040","uuid":"5bf8bec0-d4ae-43e0-b3a0-0fb356c0b5ad","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C70B6B8894EA86358A8D737C99F93AB8699A8A98\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Users must be prevented from changing installation options.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220857","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220857","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220857","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-220857r1051032_rule","rule_id":"SV-220857","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000315","rule_title":"The Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> \"Always install with elevated privileges\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: AlwaysInstallElevated\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Standard user accounts must not be granted elevated privileges. Enabling Windows Installer to elevate privileges when installing applications can allow malicious persons and applications to gain full control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63325","SV-77815","CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"8363","uuid":"57b1eaa4-ae67-480a-86a5-7d69fb7a741c","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 77E55B435A6ED684C56564F6EFA9D540B616C3C6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220858","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220858","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220858","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220858r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220858","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000320","rule_title":"Users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> \"Prevent Internet Explorer security prompt for Windows Installer scripts\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: SafeForScripting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Web-based programs may attempt to install malicious software on a system.  Ensuring users are notified if a web-based program attempts to install software allows them to refuse the installation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63329","SV-77819","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6448","uuid":"d21b2b09-7ae2-41d7-abb8-66766b88ceba","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B7C213E8CAEEBFE0B3D62BC5E63DC8ECA23AEB10\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220859","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220859","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220859","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","rule_id_src":"SV-220859r991591_rule","rule_id":"SV-220859","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000325","rule_title":"Automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Logon Options >> \"Sign-in last interactive user automatically after a system-initiated restart\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DisableAutomaticRestartSignOn\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows can be configured to automatically sign the user back in after a Windows Update restart.  Some protections are in place to help ensure this is done in a secure fashion; however, disabling this will prevent the caching of credentials for this purpose and also ensure the user is aware of the restart.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-77823","V-63333","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6904","uuid":"5642e440-0378-4f72-883c-aec0e15d5dc4","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D048F8E55BC4B25AA7896668003C4B5E061C5373\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart must be disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220860","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220860","title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220860","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","rule_id_src":"SV-220860r958422_rule","rule_id":"SV-220860","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000326","rule_title":"PowerShell script block logging must be enabled on Windows 10.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows PowerShell >> \"Turn on PowerShell Script Block Logging\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\ScriptBlockLogging\\\n\nValue Name: EnableScriptBlockLogging\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling PowerShell script block logging will record detailed information from the processing of PowerShell commands and scripts.  This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-68819","SV-83411","CCI-000135"],"reference_identifier":"6161","uuid":"19590de7-3866-4d5e-be15-cc9d51069c18","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 995CEE59CA9ABC9B1CB2A125230BB9CF89FDA2C6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'PowerShell script block logging must be enabled on Windows 10.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220862","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220862","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220862","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","rule_id_src":"SV-220862r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-220862","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000330","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Basic authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> \"Allow Basic authentication\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain text passwords that could be used to compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63335","SV-77825","CCI-000877"],"reference_identifier":"2818","uuid":"ce1076df-b1bd-4755-93be-d606fff29348","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220863","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220863","title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220863","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","rule_id_src":"SV-220863r958848_rule","rule_id":"SV-220863","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000335","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not allow unencrypted traffic.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> \"Allow unencrypted traffic\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowUnencryptedTraffic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unencrypted remote access to a system can allow sensitive information to be compromised.  Windows remote management connections must be encrypted to prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-77829","V-63339","CCI-002890","CCI-003123"],"reference_identifier":"9234","uuid":"9fc603f1-88d9-426a-81f4-83fff73bb556","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1FA39A68AA9F9967E0D3EC2CA90714FA1A3A1356\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not allow unencrypted traffic.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220865","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220865","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220865","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","rule_id_src":"SV-220865r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-220865","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000345","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not use Basic authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Service >> \"Allow Basic authentication\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nSeverity Override Guidance: The AO can allow the severity override if they have reviewed the overall protection. This would only be allowed temporarily for implementation as documented and approved. \n\u2026.\nAllowing Basic authentication to be used for the sole creation of Office 365 DoD tenants.\n\u2026.\nA documented mechanism and or script that can disable Basic authentication once administration completes. \n\u2026.\nUse of a Privileged Access Workstation (PAW) and adherence to the Clean Source principle for administration.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain text passwords that could be used to compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-77837","V-63347","CCI-000877"],"reference_identifier":"5204","uuid":"a860cab4-3b6b-4688-bc58-d345cdee7baa","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220866","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220866","title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220866","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","rule_id_src":"SV-220866r958848_rule","rule_id":"SV-220866","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000350","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not allow unencrypted traffic.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Service >> \"Allow unencrypted traffic\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: AllowUnencryptedTraffic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unencrypted remote access to a system can allow sensitive information to be compromised.  Windows remote management connections must be encrypted to prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63369","SV-77859","CCI-002890","CCI-003123"],"reference_identifier":"7319","uuid":"4308fa4a-fcc9-40e2-a3e8-215aef660709","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C0A82497E24A82E6CCB4E65F531D59E720E2CA9D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not allow unencrypted traffic.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220867","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220867","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220867","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-220867r1051033_rule","rule_id":"SV-220867","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000355","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not store RunAs credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Service >> \"Disallow WinRM from storing RunAs credentials\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: DisableRunAs\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Storage of administrative credentials could allow unauthorized access. Disallowing the storage of RunAs credentials for Windows Remote Management will prevent them from being used with plug-ins.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63375","SV-77865","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"5972","uuid":"7ea35b36-68c0-4cd5-901b-41829cb662e8","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 66DF37D05F4AE739B615C70D266DBC52D8EAFD8B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not store RunAs credentials.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220868","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220868","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220868","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","rule_id_src":"SV-220868r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-220868","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000360","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Digest authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> \"Disallow Digest authentication\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowDigest\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Digest authentication is not as strong as other options and may be subject to man-in-the-middle attacks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63341","SV-77831","CCI-000877"],"reference_identifier":"3331","uuid":"c9d42c08-77c4-4453-92fa-2c0aacffd862","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220869","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220869","title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220869","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009","rule_id_src":"SV-220869r958400_rule","rule_id":"SV-220869","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000365","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to prevent Windows apps from being activated by voice while the system is locked.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> App Privacy >> \"Let Windows apps activate with voice while the system is locked\" to \"Enabled\" with \u201cDefault for all Apps:\u201d set to \u201cForce Deny\u201d. \n\nThe requirement is NA if the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> App Privacy >> \"Let Windows apps activate with voice\" is configured to \"Enabled\" with \u201cDefault for all Apps:\u201d set to \u201cForce Deny\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting requires v1903 or later of Windows 10; it is NA for prior versions.  The setting is NA when the \u201cAllow voice activation\u201d policy is configured to disallow applications to be activated with voice for all users.\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppPrivacy\\\n\nValue Name: LetAppsActivateWithVoiceAboveLock\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)\n\nIf the following registry value exists and is configured as specified, requirement is NA. \n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppPrivacy\\\n\nValue Name: LetAppsActivateWithVoice\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing Windows apps to be activated by voice from the lock screen could allow for unauthorized use. Requiring logon will ensure the apps are only used by authorized personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-94719","SV-104549","CCI-000056"],"reference_identifier":"5213","uuid":"9df875ba-5053-4420-aa93-8bf81f5f06f0","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CC34EBCBB70BFD73A4A77F3DB68E6708B3DB5105\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to prevent Windows apps from being activated by voice while the system is locked.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220870","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220870","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220870","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220870r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220870","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000370","rule_title":"The convenience PIN for Windows 10 must be disabled.","fix_text":"Disable the convenience PIN sign-in. \n\nIf this needs to be corrected configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Logon >> Set \"Turn on convenience PIN sign-in\" to \"Disabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\n\nValue Name: AllowDomainPINLogon\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue data: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy controls whether a domain user can sign in using a convenience PIN to prevent enabling (Password Stuffer).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-99559","SV-108663","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4132","uuid":"2372b19b-b54e-4e88-8d1f-3ea90bd27c98","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0CDB37BFA0FE4A1DEA6E5748D47A57EF600D5A0A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The convenience PIN for Windows 10 must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220871","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220871","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220871","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220871r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220871","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000385","rule_title":"Windows Ink Workspace must be configured to disallow access above the lock.","fix_text":"Disable the convenience PIN sign-in. \n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Ink Workspace >> Set \"Allow Windows Ink Workspace\" to \"Enabled\u201d and set Options \"On, but disallow access above lock\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsInkWorkspace\n\nValue Name: AllowWindowsInkWorkspace\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue data: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This action secures Windows Ink, which contains applications and features oriented toward pen computing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108665","V-99561","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8752","uuid":"c23de180-fc90-42ca-8fed-f76fc27631b8","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C3CCA05E73821E15B7C8AFAA03075566E55843A2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Ink Workspace must be configured to disallow access above the lock.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220872","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220872","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220872","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220872r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220872","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000390","rule_title":"Windows 10 should be configured to prevent users from receiving suggestions for third-party or additional applications.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Cloud Content >> \"Do not suggest third-party content in Windows spotlight\" to \"Enabled","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding: \n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CloudContent\\\n\nValue Name: DisableThirdPartySuggestions\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows spotlight features may suggest apps and content from third-party software publishers in addition to Microsoft apps and content.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-99563","SV-108667","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4431","uuid":"3416a3dc-cd9d-4231-88f2-75667be4c7c5","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2E7D1AD24F81E82DAA6FA432B02B18FA07755888\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 should be configured to prevent users from receiving suggestions for third-party or additional applications.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220902","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220902","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220902","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-220902r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-220902","rule_version":"WN10-EP-000310","rule_title":"Windows 10 Kernel (Direct Memory Access) DMA Protection must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Kernel DMA Protection >> \"Enumeration policy for external devices incompatible with Kernel DMA Protection\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Enumeration Policy\" set to \"Block All\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA prior to v1803 of Windows 10.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Kernel DMA Protection\n\nValue Name: DeviceEnumerationPolicy\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Kernel DMA Protection to protect PCs against drive-by Direct Memory Access (DMA) attacks using PCI hot plug devices connected to Thunderbolt\u2122 3 ports. Drive-by DMA attacks can lead to disclosure of sensitive information residing on a PC, or even injection of malware that allows attackers to bypass the lock screen or control PCs remotely.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108661","V-99557","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"3655","uuid":"635ef5f1-7fbf-4974-a6fb-89377da9b6c0","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 82E660FD550B583AC03CA20E13A7A46D5A568FD1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 10 Kernel (Direct Memory Access) DMA Protection must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220903","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220903","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220903","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-220903r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-220903","rule_version":"WN10-PK-000005","rule_title":"The DoD Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store.","fix_text":"Install the DoD Root CA certificates:\nDoD Root CA 3\nDoD Root CA 4\nDoD Root CA 5\nDoD Root CA 6\n\nThe InstallRoot tool is available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. Certificate bundles published by the PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the DoD Root CA certificates are installed as Trusted Root Certification Authorities.\n\nThe certificates and thumbprints referenced below apply to unclassified systems; refer to PKE documentation for other networks.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\root | Where Subject -Like \"*DoD*\" | FL Subject, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\" and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nNotAfter: 12/30/2029\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 4, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\nNotAfter: 7/25/2032\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 5, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\nNotAfter: 6/14/2041\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 6, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US \nThumbprint : D37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEF\nNotAfter: 1/24/2053\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to \"Trusted Root Certification Authorities >> Certificates\".\n\nFor each of the DoD Root CA certificates noted below:\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the DoD Root CA certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nDoD Root CA 3\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nValid to: Sunday, December 30, 2029\n\nDoD Root CA 4\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\nValid to: Sunday, July 25, 2032\n\nDoD Root CA 5\nThumbprint: 4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\nValid to: Friday, June 14, 2041\n\nDoD Root CA 6\nThumbprint : D37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEF\n Valid to: Friday, January 24, 2053","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure secure DoD websites and DoD-signed code are properly validated, the system must trust the DoD Root Certificate Authorities (CAs). The DoD root certificates will ensure the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the DoD CAs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63579","SV-78069","CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"8016","uuid":"ba5fabdd-c467-4395-846d-386e0c357dc8","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F63392C7F14BD6055798EF92D0A8D488F5D7BA10\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The DoD Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220904","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220904","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220904","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-220904r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-220904","rule_version":"WN10-PK-000010","rule_title":"The External Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the ECA Root CA certificate on unclassified systems.\nECA Root CA 4\n\nThe InstallRoot tool is available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. Certificate bundles published by the PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the ECA Root CA certificates are installed on unclassified systems as Trusted Root Certification Authorities.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\root | Where Subject -Like \"*ECA*\" | FL Subject, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\" and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=ECA Root CA 4, OU=ECA, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 73E8BB08E337D6A5A6AEF90CFFDD97D9176CB582\nNotAfter: 12/30/2029\n\nAlternately use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to \"Trusted Root Certification Authorities >> Certificates\".\n\nFor each of the ECA Root CA certificates noted below:\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" Tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the ECA Root CA certificate below is not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nECA Root CA 4\nThumbprint: 73E8BB08E337D6A5A6AEF90CFFDD97D9176CB582\nValid to: Sunday, December 30, 2029","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure secure websites protected with External Certificate Authority (ECA) server certificates are properly validated, the system must trust the ECA Root CAs. The ECA root certificates will ensure the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the External CAs. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63583","SV-78073","CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"5491","uuid":"6302138d-5a12-4c17-a249-272c64d9cecd","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F3E612D3C45F3F1F77E89DACACD006BE75479E2E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The External Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store on unclassified systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220905","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220905","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220905","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-220905r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-220905","rule_version":"WN10-PK-000015","rule_title":"The DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\n\nDoD Root CA 3 - DoD Interoperability Root CA 2 - 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477 \n                  \nThe certificates can be installed using the InstallRoot tool. The tool and user guide are available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the DoD Interoperability cross-certificates are installed on unclassified systems as Untrusted Certificates.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where {$_.Issuer -Like \"*DoD Interoperability*\" -and $_.Subject -Like \"*DoD*\"} | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\", \"Issuer\", and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=DoD Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\nNotAfter: 11/16/2024 \n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Untrusted Certificates >> Certificates.\n\nFor each certificate with \"DoD Root CA\u2026\" under \"Issued To\" and \"DoD Interoperability Root CA\u2026\" under \"Issued By\":\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nIssued To: DoD Root CA 3\nIssued By: DoD Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint: 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\nValid to: Wednesday, November 16, 2024","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DoD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DoD Root CAs, the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63587","SV-78077","CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"8960","uuid":"5df7d977-75a8-4c5b-a519-b1a25d0b96e9","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220906","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220906","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220906","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-220906r1081051_rule","rule_id":"SV-220906","rule_version":"WN10-PK-000020","rule_title":"The US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\nDOD Root CA 3 - US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2  9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nIssued To: DOD Root CA 6\nIssued By: US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint: D471CA32F7A692CE6CBB6196BD3377FE4DBCD106\nNotAfter: 7/18/2026\n\nThe certificates can be installed using the InstallRoot tool. The tool and user guide are available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate is installed on unclassified systems as an Untrusted Certificate.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where Issuer -Like \"*CCEB Interoperability*\" | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\", \"Issuer\", and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=DOD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025 9:56:22 AM\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", then click \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", then click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", then click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", then click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Untrusted Certificates >> Certificates.\n\nFor each certificate with \"US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA \u2026\" under \"Issued By\":\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificate below is not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DOD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025 9:56:22 AM                                                          \nSubject: CN=DOD Root CA 6, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: D471CA32F7A692CE6CBB6196BD3377FE4DBCD106\nNotAfter: 7/18/2026 9:56:22 AM","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DOD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DOD Root CAs, the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78079","V-63589","CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"5007","uuid":"3a74f359-9ff1-4cbd-a5e6-2e2d7f3771de","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2BF1C0C937D0F3421284F5B769096F68339F1158\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220907","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220907","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220907","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220907r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220907","rule_version":"WN10-RG-000005","rule_title":"Default permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE registry hive must be maintained.","fix_text":"Maintain the default permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE registry hive.\n\nThe default permissions of the higher level keys are noted below.\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SECURITY\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Special - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nMicrosoft has also given Read permission to the SOFTWARE and SYSTEM registry keys in later versions of Windows 10 to the following SID.\n\nS-1-15-3-1024-1065365936-1281604716-3511738428-1654721687-432734479-3232135806-4053264122-3456934681","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the default registry permissions for the keys note below of the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE hive.\n\nIf any non-privileged groups such as Everyone, Users or Authenticated Users have greater than Read permission, this is a finding.\n\nRun \"Regedit\".\nRight click on the registry areas noted below.\nSelect \"Permissions...\" and the \"Advanced\" button.\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SECURITY\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Special - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nOther subkeys under the noted keys may also be sampled. There may be some instances where non-privileged groups have greater than Read permission.\n\nMicrosoft has given Read permission to the SOFTWARE and SYSTEM registry keys in later versions of Windows 10 to the following SID, this is currently not a finding.\n\nS-1-15-3-1024-1065365936-1281604716-3511738428-1654721687-432734479-3232135806-4053264122-3456934681\n\nIf the defaults have not been changed, these are not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The registry is integral to the function, security, and stability of the Windows system.  Changing the system's registry permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78083","V-63593","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"6758","uuid":"8db4683e-d5c3-49be-846b-bb31d6bfe702","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220909","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220909","title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220909","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","rule_id_src":"SV-220909r958504_rule","rule_id":"SV-220909","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000010","rule_title":"The built-in guest account must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Guest account status\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Guest account status\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system faces an increased vulnerability threat if the built-in guest account is not disabled.  This account is a known account that exists on all Windows systems and cannot be deleted.  This account is initialized during the installation of the operating system with no password assigned.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63611","SV-78101","CCI-000804"],"reference_identifier":"5163","uuid":"a59998f4-e9f0-4917-b786-93eee21682cd","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 211CA13DAF4C5FD178FFFD5E2D045613928DE16F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The built-in guest account must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220910","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220910","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220910","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220910r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220910","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000015","rule_title":"Local accounts with blank passwords must be restricted to prevent access from the network.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Limit local account use of blank passwords to console logon only\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LimitBlankPasswordUse\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An account without a password can allow unauthorized access to a system as only the username would be required.  Password policies should prevent accounts with blank passwords from existing on a system.  However, if a local account with a blank password did exist, enabling this setting will prevent network access, limiting the account to local console logon only.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63617","SV-78107","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3902","uuid":"1e4f28c4-617f-4827-9f6a-e27fa8088a97","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7DDA03F6F32ADA1989AC8BCAE0D8AB3232BBDC81\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Local accounts with blank passwords must be restricted to prevent access from the network.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220911","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220911","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220911","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220911r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220911","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000020","rule_title":"The built-in administrator account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" to a name other than \"Administrator\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" is set to \"Administrator\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in administrator account is a well-known account subject to attack.  Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78109","V-63619","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8074","uuid":"e52f1ba0-5790-4ca9-b0bf-3b9f9875a577","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 015FD92AB29648D97E6BC69D0092726D32758573\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The built-in administrator account must be renamed.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220912","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220912","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220912","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220912r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220912","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000025","rule_title":"The built-in guest account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" to a name other than \"Guest\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" is set to \"Guest\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in guest account is a well-known user account on all Windows systems and, as initially installed, does not require a password.  This can allow access to system resources by unauthorized users.  Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78115","V-63625","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9156","uuid":"3c964a08-de44-41f7-948d-4633a56a4846","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BA609255921043B683FD7F0044DA21527E5DDBE7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The built-in guest account must be renamed.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220913","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220913","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220913","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-220913r958442_rule","rule_id":"SV-220913","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000030","rule_title":"Audit policy using subcategories must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: SCENoApplyLegacyAuditPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.  This setting allows administrators to enable more precise auditing capabilities.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63635","SV-78125","CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"7793","uuid":"fe00c87b-c083-48b3-9276-1090575dff96","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9A9E31CE71120E21B4AD8BF3A0F8A7B35C092A4D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Audit policy using subcategories must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220914","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220914","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220914","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-220914r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-220914","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000035","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted or signed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSignOrSeal\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted.  If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted and signed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63639","SV-78129","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"5215","uuid":"5c71217c-673b-47a4-9e66-1dd77dc4844e","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 13A4883061DA1210C688338C9B7B183B7D2783D3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted or signed.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220915","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220915","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220915","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-220915r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-220915","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000040","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted when possible.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Digitally encrypt secure channel data (when possible)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SealSecureChannel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted.  If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78133","V-63643","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"6182","uuid":"be60dcc1-34ad-45f8-a5e6-3ff64ce4f105","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F49BB183C60507B7CF3A5BD1591E8CEC1F026B3D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted when possible.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220916","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220916","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220916","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-220916r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-220916","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000045","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be signed when possible.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Digitally sign secure channel data (when possible)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SignSecureChannel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but the channel is not integrity checked.  If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be signed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78137","V-63647","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"3050","uuid":"73b67716-5e62-4b94-b60f-10185ea297a5","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DB2E558529A768438B881F00ED5879515C314802\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Outgoing secure channel traffic must be signed when possible.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220917","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220917","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220917","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220917r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220917","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000050","rule_title":"The computer account password must not be prevented from being reset.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Disable machine account password changes\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordChange\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis.  Disabling automatic password changes can make the system more vulnerable to malicious access.  Frequent password changes can be a significant safeguard for your system.  A new password for the computer account will be generated every 30 days.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63653","SV-78143","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7207","uuid":"239bbd7b-8876-4cbf-b72d-c52a21bf8ae3","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3B0100428F3A71F6CFB17502EAC783F502451103\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The computer account password must not be prevented from being reset.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220918","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220918","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220918","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220918r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220918","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000055","rule_title":"The maximum age for machine account passwords must be configured to 30 days or less.","fix_text":"This is the default configuration for this setting (30 days).\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Maximum machine account password age\" to \"30\" or less (excluding 0 which is unacceptable).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is the default configuration for this setting (30 days).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: MaximumPasswordAge\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x0000001e (30)  (or less, excluding 0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis.  This setting controls the maximum password age that a machine account may have.  This setting must be set to no more than 30 days, ensuring the machine changes its password monthly.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78151","V-63661","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9099","uuid":"6a6b2741-f63c-4160-8bcd-6af781ab75eb","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9784C69526AD2307EB407D8CFA2B3FA5496F78BD\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The maximum age for machine account passwords must be configured to 30 days or less.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220919","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220919","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220919","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-220919r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-220919","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000060","rule_title":"The system must be configured to require a strong session key.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Require strong (Windows 2000 or Later) session key\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireStrongKey\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n \nWarning: This setting may prevent a system from being joined to a domain if not configured consistently between systems.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A computer connecting to a domain controller will establish a secure channel.  Requiring strong session keys enforces 128-bit encryption between systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63665","SV-78155","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"5369","uuid":"2fdbe586-e531-4bce-8701-65b094163687","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 327009244EB9CA8170EF0E9351B76922A468820F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to require a strong session key.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220920","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220920","title":"SRG-OS-000029-GPOS-00010","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220920","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000029-GPOS-00010","rule_id_src":"SV-220920r958402_rule","rule_id":"SV-220920","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000070","rule_title":"The machine inactivity limit must be set to 15 minutes, locking the system with the screensaver.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Machine inactivity limit\" to \"900\" seconds\" or less, excluding \"0\" which is effectively disabled.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: InactivityTimeoutSecs\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000384 (900) (or less, excluding \"0\" which is effectively disabled)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and should be locked when unattended.  The screen saver should be set at a maximum of 15 minutes and be password protected.  This protects critical and sensitive data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78159","V-63669","CCI-000057"],"reference_identifier":"1689","uuid":"b3b087dd-19dd-4c1b-a252-7bf9d2bd6572","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 73E517547E3D7730625842F5C18DBE139CF5AEE6\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The machine inactivity limit must be set to 15 minutes, locking the system with the screensaver.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220921","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220921","title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220921","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","rule_id_src":"SV-220921r958390_rule","rule_id":"SV-220921","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000075","rule_title":"The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Message text for users attempting to log on\" to the following.\n\nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants.  Such communications and work product are private and confidential.  See User Agreement for details.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeText\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: \nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants.  Such communications and work product are private and confidential.  See User Agreement for details.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63675","SV-78165","CCI-000048","CCI-000050","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"2002","uuid":"809093e5-d5ae-40de-a243-37fe0a339d92","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FFAB01BFCA2754408E2AB0FC8FC28F36A12F29EC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220922","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220922","title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220922","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","rule_id_src":"SV-220922r958390_rule","rule_id":"SV-220922","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000080","rule_title":"The Windows dialog box title for the legal banner must be configured.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Message title for users attempting to log on\" to \"DoD Notice and Consent Banner\", \"US Department of Defense Warning Statement\", or a site-defined equivalent.\n\nIf a site-defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the banner text required in WN10-SO-000075.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeCaption\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: See message title above\n\n\"DoD Notice and Consent Banner\", \"US Department of Defense Warning Statement\" or a site-defined equivalent, this is a finding.\n\nIf a site-defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the banner text required in WN10-SO-000075.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78171","V-63681","CCI-000048","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"5271","uuid":"438f6b3a-54c0-44b7-92a5-bddac637454d","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220923","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220923","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220923","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220923r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220923","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000085","rule_title":"Caching of logon credentials must be limited.","fix_text":"This is the default configuration for this setting (10 logons to cache).\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Number of previous logons to cache (in case domain controller is not available)\" to \"10\" logons or less.\n\nThis setting only applies to domain-joined systems, however, it is configured by default on all systems.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is the default configuration for this setting (10 logons to cache).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  CachedLogonsCount\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  10 (or less)\n\nThis setting only applies to domain-joined systems, however, it is configured by default on all systems.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The default Windows configuration caches the last logon credentials for users who log on interactively to a system.  This feature is provided for system availability reasons, such as the user's machine being disconnected from the network or domain controllers being unavailable.  Even though the credential cache is well-protected, if a system is attacked, an unauthorized individual may isolate the password to a domain user account using a password-cracking program and gain access to the domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78177","V-63687","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3471","uuid":"0f490a29-4518-40b9-9482-8a60531cdc50","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1C3427632E917E06F1AAE526828A37EBCBB2FFA8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Caching of logon credentials must be limited.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220924","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220924","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220924","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220924r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220924","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000095","rule_title":"The Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Smart card removal behavior\" to  \"Lock Workstation\" or \"Force Logoff\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  SCRemoveOption\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  1 (Lock Workstation) or 2 (Force Logoff)\n\nThis can be left not configured or set to \"No action\" on workstations with the following conditions.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\n-The setting cannot be configured due to mission needs, or because it interferes with applications.\n-Policy must be in place that users manually lock workstations when leaving them unattended.\n-The screen saver is properly configured to lock as required.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked.  Configuring a system to lock when a smart card is removed will ensure the system is inaccessible when unattended.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63697","SV-78187","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8882","uuid":"42ba6112-5432-4e5d-b1ee-05b625b76370","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 292D10AA7F6E33FD0F3765A171EF3CE4B4189081\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220925","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220925","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220925","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-220925r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-220925","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000100","rule_title":"The Windows SMB client must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (always)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations.  Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks.  If this policy is enabled, the SMB client will only communicate with an SMB server that performs SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63703","SV-78193","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"7090","uuid":"43a995b6-6dd7-4932-9edf-06e4e7de4f2c","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4E9B800A8A756C63CA460AE4E904F5DDAB55887C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows SMB client must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220926","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220926","title":"SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220926","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042","rule_id_src":"SV-220926r987796_rule","rule_id":"SV-220926","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000110","rule_title":"Unencrypted passwords must not be sent to third-party SMB Servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft network client: Send unencrypted password to third-party SMB servers\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  EnablePlainTextPassword\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some non-Microsoft SMB servers only support unencrypted (plain text) password authentication.  Sending plain text passwords across the network, when authenticating to an SMB server, reduces the overall security of the environment.  Check with the vendor of the SMB server to see if there is a way to support encrypted password authentication.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63711","SV-78201","CCI-000197"],"reference_identifier":"8676","uuid":"d5c881c9-c611-44d0-90a5-27b26e9b567f","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220927","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220927","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220927","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-220927r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-220927","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000120","rule_title":"The Windows SMB server must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft network server: Digitally sign communications (always)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations.  Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks.  If this policy is enabled, the SMB server will only communicate with an SMB client that performs SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78209","V-63719","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"5986","uuid":"ae4c68f4-afc3-43a3-ae61-67ff9ceefcfb","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 07BCFF05FAA38257A571D7AF63C277FA8BF1E2DB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows SMB server must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220928","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220928","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220928","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220928r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220928","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000140","rule_title":"Anonymous SID/Name translation must not be allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous SID/Name translation can provide sensitive information for accessing a system.  Only authorized users must be able to perform such translations.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63739","SV-78229","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1861","uuid":"557a90cf-89a8-44a7-a099-cef7a628e610","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 79F9E50B0EA0977E9C6CC2B0BCD184F721ADE452\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Anonymous SID/Name translation must not be allowed.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220929","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220929","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220929","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220929r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220929","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000145","rule_title":"Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts must not be allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictAnonymousSAM\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts allows anonymous log on users (null session connections) to list all accounts names, thus providing a list of potential points to attack the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78235","V-63745","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5460","uuid":"6dbb0756-9728-4ae5-ba7e-8440f27298a8","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8B369CE0CEFAD8AB43C57BB350D3F7CCA2516946\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts must not be allowed.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220930","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220930","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220930","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-220930r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-220930","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000150","rule_title":"Anonymous enumeration of shares must be restricted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts and shares\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictAnonymous\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous logon users (null session connections) to list all account names and enumerate all shared resources can provide a map of potential points to attack the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63749","SV-78239","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"1489","uuid":"e3bf4529-e1da-4843-aa08-9a0b72f7d4ca","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 480035DED3940EBA790A8887D87EB61BF7115DB1\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Anonymous enumeration of shares must be restricted.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220931","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220931","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220931","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220931r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220931","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000160","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent anonymous users from having the same rights as the Everyone group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: EveryoneIncludesAnonymous\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Access by anonymous users must be restricted.  If this setting is enabled, then anonymous users have the same rights and permissions as the built-in Everyone group.  Anonymous users must not have these permissions or rights.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63755","SV-78245","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2920","uuid":"45e78090-c28b-4d51-9b5f-98a5665c44af","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4DD07A8A902D2A4C4AEEB1B5F325348BF609CB59\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to prevent anonymous users from having the same rights as the Everyone group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220932","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220932","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220932","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-220932r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-220932","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000165","rule_title":"Anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares must be restricted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Restrict anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictNullSessAccess\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous access to named pipes or shares provides the potential for unauthorized system access.  This setting restricts access to those defined in \"Network access: Named Pipes that can be accessed anonymously\" and \"Network access: Shares that can be accessed anonymously\",  both of which must be blank under other requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78249","V-63759","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"8079","uuid":"4a8d162a-87c5-4337-92a6-2bdfd7a117f3","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2349D8F1C41480E36F8C1F16F1C531384ECCDDC0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares must be restricted.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220933","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220933","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220933","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220933r1081053_rule","rule_id":"SV-220933","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000167","rule_title":"Remote calls to the Security Account Manager (SAM) must be restricted to Administrators.","fix_text":"Navigate to the policy Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Restrict clients allowed to make remote calls to SAM\".\n\nSelect \"Edit Security\" to configure the \"Security descriptor:\".\n\nAdd \"Administrators\" in \"Group or user names:\" if it is not already listed (this is the default).\n\nSelect \"Administrators\" in \"Group or user names:\".\n\nSelect \"Allow\" for \"Remote Access\" in \"Permissions for \"Administrators\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nThe \"Security descriptor:\" must be populated with \"O:BAG:BAD:(A;;RC;;;BA) for the policy to be enforced.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows 10 v1507 LTSB version does not include this setting, it is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictRemoteSAM\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: O:BAG:BAD:(A;;RC;;;BA)                                                   \n\nIf a domain application account such as for a management tool requires this user right, this is not a finding.\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows SAM stores users' passwords. Restricting remote rpc connections to the SAM to Administrators helps protect those credentials.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-86393","V-71769","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8378","uuid":"c0106b1d-2694-4caf-8a7e-6e4d1bdd28fa","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B97EE392AEE5609F05AEFDE1879A335DC8102841\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote calls to the Security Account Manager (SAM) must be restricted to Administrators.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220934","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220934","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220934","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220934r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220934","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000180","rule_title":"NTLM must be prevented from falling back to a Null session.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Allow LocalSystem NULL session fallback\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: allownullsessionfallback\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"NTLM sessions that are allowed to fall back to Null (unauthenticated) sessions may gain unauthorized access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63765","SV-78255","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2049","uuid":"d76a829a-50f3-4b9d-9a53-300bd28bdc58","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 45B783C9C025809D15D4817A989B3E3E76909028\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'NTLM must be prevented from falling back to a Null session.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220935","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220935","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220935","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220935r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220935","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000185","rule_title":"PKU2U authentication using online identities must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Allow PKU2U authentication requests to this computer to use online identities\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\pku2u\\\n\nValue Name: AllowOnlineID\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"PKU2U is a peer-to-peer authentication protocol.   This setting prevents online identities from authenticating to domain-joined systems.  Authentication will be centrally managed with Windows user accounts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78257","V-63767","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4865","uuid":"4b27be88-c84b-4e21-b845-0f2f7ca74a8c","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CCE52F4714656B80DADF46DB1B7682666B795BB1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'PKU2U authentication using online identities must be prevented.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220936","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220936","title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220936","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","rule_id_src":"SV-220936r971535_rule","rule_id":"SV-220936","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000190","rule_title":"Kerberos encryption types must be configured to prevent the use of DES and RC4 encryption suites.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Configure encryption types allowed for Kerberos\" to \"Enabled\" with only the following selected:\n\nAES128_HMAC_SHA1\nAES256_HMAC_SHA1\nFuture encryption types","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Kerberos\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SupportedEncryptionTypes\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x7ffffff8 (2147483640)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Certain encryption types are no longer considered secure.  This setting configures a minimum encryption type for Kerberos, preventing the use of the DES and RC4 encryption suites.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78285","V-63795","CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"9947","uuid":"d7f8af6a-9a52-426d-a4c2-e4cc19241829","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 78112FFC5A629518C36A2A81562DAE99CFD64EF1\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Kerberos encryption types must be configured to prevent the use of DES and RC4 encryption suites.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220937","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220937","title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220937","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","rule_id_src":"SV-220937r1051034_rule","rule_id":"SV-220937","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000195","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent the storage of the LAN Manager hash of passwords.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Do not store LAN Manager hash value on next password change\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: NoLMHash\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The LAN Manager hash uses a weak encryption algorithm and there are several tools available that use this hash to retrieve account passwords. This setting controls whether or not a LAN Manager hash of the password is stored in the SAM the next time the password is changed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78287","V-63797","CCI-004062","CCI-000196"],"reference_identifier":"6641","uuid":"2a71d841-17bc-4740-8370-6933b6640c1d","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 615FFAA3E5582C06D81A1C4CDC52A41A8290CDCB\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to prevent the storage of the LAN Manager hash of passwords.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220938","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220938","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220938","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220938r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220938","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000205","rule_title":"The LanMan authentication level must be set to send NTLMv2 response only, and to refuse LM and NTLM.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: LAN Manager authentication level\" to \"Send NTLMv2 response only. Refuse LM & NTLM\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LmCompatibilityLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 5","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Kerberos v5 authentication protocol is the default for authentication of users who are logging on to domain accounts.  NTLM, which is less secure, is retained in later Windows versions  for compatibility with clients and servers that are running earlier versions of Windows or applications that still use it.  It is also used to authenticate logons to stand-alone computers that are running later versions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78291","V-63801","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3736","uuid":"56275a9a-006c-4b97-98d6-09e75d638072","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E4BA80084BB796ADF259E1800283A1B48F70FA60\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The LanMan authentication level must be set to send NTLMv2 response only, and to refuse LM and NTLM.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220939","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220939","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220939","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220939r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220939","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000210","rule_title":"The system must be configured to the required LDAP client signing level.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: LDAP client signing requirements\" to \"Negotiate signing\" at a minimum.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LDAP\\\n\nValue Name: LDAPClientIntegrity\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the signing requirements for LDAP clients.  This setting must be set to Negotiate signing or Require signing, depending on the environment and type of LDAP server in use.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78293","V-63803","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9548","uuid":"661d38ec-f415-4771-85a9-ae2baba12f0a","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2742CED49C59181E384E1632D28BECB574D82808\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to the required LDAP client signing level.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220940","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220940","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220940","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220940r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220940","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000215","rule_title":"The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based clients.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) clients\" to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinClientSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with RPC sessions.  All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63805","SV-78295","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7083","uuid":"db5069c5-ec9b-4789-8c97-b6ce3811a0ed","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9797448B1D979800AF9402BE81CCB27BA1F124A1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based clients.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220941","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220941","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220941","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220941r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220941","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000220","rule_title":"The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) servers\" to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinServerSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with RPC sessions.  All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78297","V-63807","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4115","uuid":"b8ef44df-7037-4826-9fe3-1194ce2e185f","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 900CEF4A8C313353FA79A116B5ED8A309AEC6DD8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based servers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220942","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220942","title":"SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220942","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223","rule_id_src":"SV-220942r1137699_rule","rule_id":"SV-220942","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000230","rule_title":"The system must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"System cryptography: Use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\FIPSAlgorithmPolicy\\\n\nValue Name: Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n \nWarning: Clients with this setting enabled will not be able to communicate via digitally encrypted or signed protocols with servers that do not support these algorithms.  Both the browser and web server must be configured to use TLS otherwise the browser will not be able to connect to a secure site.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting ensures that the system uses algorithms that are FIPS-compliant for encryption, hashing, and signing.  FIPS-compliant algorithms meet specific standards established by the U.S. Government and must be the algorithms used for all OS encryption functions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63811","SV-78301","CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"1156","uuid":"c0e0ddae-438f-4709-bc71-1ce2aaae5dfb","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D9CCD7C7CAAAA6905ACD04E420C397AA9B14EE24\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220943","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220943","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220943","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220943r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220943","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000240","rule_title":"The default permissions of global system objects must be increased.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"System objects: Strengthen default permissions of internal system objects (e.g. Symbolic links)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\\n\nValue Name: ProtectionMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows systems maintain a global list of shared system resources such as DOS device names, mutexes, and semaphores. Each type of object is created with a default DACL that specifies who can access the objects with what permissions. If this policy is enabled, the default DACL is stronger, allowing non-admin users to read shared objects, but not modify shared objects that they did not create.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78305","V-63815","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1114","uuid":"ac1e803b-ec24-4eed-a4ec-1522381fe2c2","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 46F330ACAD5C5C678BFA9FBFC91B158784BA6064\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The default permissions of global system objects must be increased.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220944","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220944","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220944","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","rule_id_src":"SV-220944r1051035_rule","rule_id":"SV-220944","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000245","rule_title":"User Account Control approval mode for the built-in Administrator must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Admin Approval Mode for the Built-in Administrator account\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: FilterAdministratorToken\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures the built-in Administrator account so that it runs in Admin Approval Mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63817","SV-78307","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"2991","uuid":"4eb36d98-61d0-411e-865b-773ed75cfe6f","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2C8D4299DB2880D2E0BC0DD3ACC1198B4DC1B03C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'User Account Control approval mode for the built-in Administrator must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220945","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220945","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220945","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-220945r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-220945","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000250","rule_title":"User Account Control must, at minimum, prompt administrators for consent on the secure desktop.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for administrators in Admin Approval Mode\" to \"Prompt for consent on the secure desktop\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorAdmin\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2 (Prompt for consent on the secure desktop)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting configures the elevation requirements for logged on administrators to complete a task that requires raised privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63819","SV-78309","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"3574","uuid":"b56a36ff-e9a7-46a8-aded-d569106714b7","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F312D48FD82A1DDFB80BD233F5101FF5BC5905C9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'User Account Control must, at minimum, prompt administrators for consent on the secure desktop.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220946","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220946","title":"SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220946","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052","rule_id_src":"SV-220946r1153410_rule","rule_id":"SV-220946","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000251","rule_title":"Windows 10 must use multifactor authentication for local and network access to privileged and nonprivileged accounts.","fix_text":"For nondomain-joined systems, configuring Windows Hello for sign-on options is suggested based on the organization's needs and capabilities.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf all of the following settings exist and are populated, this is not a finding.\n\nComputer\\HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Calais\\Readers\nComputer\\HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Calais\\SmartCards","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without the use of multifactor authentication, the ease of access to privileged and nonprivileged functions is greatly increased. \n\nAll domain accounts must be enabled for multifactor authentication with the exception of local emergency accounts. \n\nMultifactor authentication requires using two or more factors to achieve authentication.\n\nFactors include: \n\n1) Something a user knows (e.g., password/PIN);\n2) Something a user has (e.g., cryptographic identification device, token); and\n3) Something a user is (e.g., biometric).\n\nA privileged account is defined as an information system account with authorizations of a privileged user.\n\nNetwork access is defined as access to an information system by a user (or a process acting on behalf of a user) communicating through a network (e.g., local area network, wide area network, or the internet).\n\nLocal access is defined as access to an organizational information system by a user (or process acting on behalf of a user) communicating through a direct connection without the use of a network.\n\nThe DOD CAC with DOD-approved PKI is an example of multifactor authentication.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000106-GPOS-00053, SRG-OS-000107-GPOS-00054, SRG-OS-000108-GPOS-00055","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-111577","V-102627","CCI-000765"],"reference_identifier":"1384","uuid":"417460f0-ff4d-4458-bb59-ec018da0fb2b","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DA0FD017D19A19C1021948FEDECFC481FC8E3A1D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must use multifactor authentication for local and network access to privileged and nonprivileged accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220947","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220947","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220947","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","rule_id_src":"SV-220947r1051036_rule","rule_id":"SV-220947","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000255","rule_title":"User Account Control must automatically deny elevation requests for standard users.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for standard users\" to \"Automatically deny elevation requests\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorUser\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. Denying elevation requests from standard user accounts requires tasks that need elevation to be initiated by accounts with administrative privileges. This ensures correct accounts are used on the system for privileged tasks to help mitigate credential theft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78311","V-63821","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"9412","uuid":"f6520618-51a7-49c6-8b6b-208e77d28b8a","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 250E1BF892B6317DB30C1F3B4789F4A0424708DD\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control must automatically deny elevation requests for standard users.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220948","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220948","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220948","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-220948r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-220948","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000260","rule_title":"User Account Control must be configured to detect application installations and prompt for elevation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Detect application installations and prompt for elevation\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableInstallerDetection\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting requires Windows to respond to application installation requests by prompting for credentials.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78315","V-63825","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"3055","uuid":"413ca7f6-31e0-4682-b515-841fee008a7f","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 47F013A661534E35DBFD502F4A422BC33F7C335F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control must be configured to detect application installations and prompt for elevation.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220949","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220949","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220949","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-220949r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-220949","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000265","rule_title":"User Account Control must only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSecureUIAPaths\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting configures Windows to only allow applications installed in a secure location on the file system, such as the Program Files or the Windows\\System32 folders, to run with elevated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63827","SV-78317","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"8098","uuid":"4a318aeb-9e8b-4a85-ae50-ca2782cba9fd","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C8EF9C5254900CFA2112AAD769C05A074D66C1C4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control must only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220950","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220950","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220950","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","rule_id_src":"SV-220950r1051037_rule","rule_id":"SV-220950","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000270","rule_title":"User Account Control must run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode, enabling UAC.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableLUA\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting enables UAC.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78319","V-63829","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"9906","uuid":"8c3b9f79-acbe-4da8-91a6-dad47f12e100","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EC4619BE050DCD87C74038E49DFE8DA6C831D5D5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control must run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode, enabling UAC.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220951","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220951","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220951","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-220951r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-220951","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000275","rule_title":"User Account Control must virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableVirtualization\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting configures non-UAC compliant applications to run in virtualized file and registry entries in per-user locations, allowing them to run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78321","V-63831","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"9432","uuid":"360cb9f9-59fa-4649-89a6-af4c2518a5a0","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A5CDB0A946A41CB589618C6E2137B478EA2B291A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control must virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220952","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220952","title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220952","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","rule_id_src":"SV-220952r1051038_rule","rule_id":"SV-220952","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000280","rule_title":"Passwords for enabled local Administrator accounts must be changed at least every 60 days.","fix_text":"Change the enabled local Administrator account password at least every 60 days. Windows LAPS must be used to change the built-in Administrator account password. Domain-joined systems can configure this to occur more frequently. LAPS will change the password every 30 days by default. \n\nMore information is available at:\nhttps://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/windows-it-pro-blog/by-popular-demand-windows-laps-available-now/ba-p/3788747\nhttps://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/identity/laps/laps-overview#windows-laps-supported-platforms-and-azure-ad-laps-preview-status","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If there are no enabled local Administrator accounts, this is Not Applicable.\n\nReview the password last set date for the enabled local Administrator account.\n\nOn the standalone or domain-joined workstation:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-LocalUser -Name * | Select-Object *\".\n\nIf the \"PasswordLastSet\" date is greater than \"60\" days old for the local Administrator account for administering the computer/domain, this is a finding.\n\nVerify LAPS is configured and operational. \n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> LAPS >> Password Settings >> Set to enabled. Password Complexity, large letters + small letters + numbers + special, Password Length 14, Password Age 60. If not configured as shown, this is a finding. \n\nVerify LAPS Operational logs >> Event Viewer >> Applications and Services Logs >> Microsoft >> Windows >> LAPS >> Operational. Verify LAPS policy process is completing. If it is not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The longer a password is in use, the greater the opportunity for someone to gain unauthorized knowledge of the password. A local Administrator account is not generally used and its password may not be changed as frequently as necessary. Changing the password for enabled Administrator accounts on a regular basis will limit its exposure.\n\nWindows LAPS must be used to change the built-in Administrator account password.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000199"],"reference_identifier":"7134","uuid":"ff0abedd-207b-4f6e-a099-4a3622ed1c7c","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C02A8999DDDF9A845ACBD7A3A0155979684F2902\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Passwords for enabled local Administrator accounts must be changed at least every 60 days.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220954","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220954","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220954","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220954r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220954","rule_version":"WN10-UC-000015","rule_title":"Toast notifications to the lock screen must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Start Menu and Taskbar >> Notifications >> \"Turn off toast notifications on the lock screen\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\PushNotifications\\\n\nValue Name: NoToastApplicationNotificationOnLockScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Toast notifications that are displayed on the lock screen could display sensitive information to unauthorized personnel.  Turning off this feature will limit access to the information to a logged on user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63839","SV-78329","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2791","uuid":"e919706b-822a-4988-93f1-12b255fc1e88","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D8A8436421374295953284E16BE0CFA4C31BF8AD\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Toast notifications to the lock screen must be turned off.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220955","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220955","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220955","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220955r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220955","rule_version":"WN10-UC-000020","rule_title":"Zone information must be preserved when saving attachments.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Windows to mark file attachments with their zone information.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Attachment Manager >> \"Do not preserve zone information in file attachments\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Windows to mark file attachments with their zone information.\n\nIf the registry Value Name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"2\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name: SaveZoneInformation\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preserving zone of origin (internet, intranet, local, restricted) information on file attachments allows Windows to determine risk.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63841","SV-78331","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3174","uuid":"86734327-e286-47f4-9972-62cb1b72e9a9","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 539E0CCBE3DB4463C83ACADF6DC7B4FC92F0818B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Zone information must be preserved when saving attachments.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220956","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220956","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220956","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220956r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220956","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000005","rule_title":"The Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts are granted the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right may be able to retrieve the credentials of other accounts from Credential Manager.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63843","SV-78333","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"6490","uuid":"9f2ad8d3-5d78-4c19-b8a1-867098ebc830","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F83A943CA34057ED8EB100C2D2B3D311B6A41260\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220957","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220957","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220957","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-220957r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-220957","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000010","rule_title":"The Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Remote Desktop Users groups.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Access this computer from the network\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators   \nRemote Desktop Users","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nRemote Desktop Users\n\nIf a domain application account such as for a management tool requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account, managed at the domain level, must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length and frequency of changes as defined in the Windows server STIGs.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right may access resources on the system, and must be limited to those that require it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78335","V-63845","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"2324","uuid":"1d1454e0-4eb4-490b-b217-9afe2932cb7f","stig_uuid":"af950999-fa42-4c61-9340-039117433de8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 79EBFDAE6AD9E09162BE477AB7E19065D51C4905\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Remote Desktop Users groups.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220958","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220958","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220958","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220958r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220958","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000015","rule_title":"The Act as part of the operating system user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Act as part of the operating system\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts (to include administrators), are granted the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right can assume the identity of any user and gain access to resources that user is authorized to access.  Any accounts with this right can take complete control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78337","V-63847","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"7742","uuid":"72c95ce9-ef95-41a9-930b-0877eba2f690","stig_uu