-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235739","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235739r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235739","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000022","rule_title":"Importing of search engine settings must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of search engine settings\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of search engine settings\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportSearchEngine\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allows users to import search engine settings from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the option to import search engine settings is automatically selected.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, search engine settings are not imported at first run, and users cannot import them manually.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9895","uuid":"a9e4f7cb-30cf-4899-bb56-e75dedf0b300","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6AE56A48959E8DA62A287BC2BB71779298525224\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Importing of search engine settings must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235740","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235740","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235740","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235740r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235740","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000023","rule_title":"Importing of shortcuts must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of shortcuts\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of shortcuts\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportShortcuts\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allows users to import Shortcuts from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, Shortcuts are not imported on first run.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, Shortcuts are imported on first run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9637","uuid":"99824fe0-cd89-417d-97e0-7d78a44b1952","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D7B493D59110F8F57BE42FC0DC7FE7CE9DC88F31\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Importing of shortcuts must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235741","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235741","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235741","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235741r1007485_rule","rule_id":"SV-235741","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000024","rule_title":"AutoplayAllowed must be set to disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay for websites\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay for websites\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutoplayAllowed\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy sets the media autoplay policy for websites.\n\nThe default setting \"Not configured\" respects the current media autoplay settings and lets users configure their autoplay settings.\n\nSetting to \"Enabled\" sets media autoplay to \"Allow\". All websites are allowed to autoplay media. Users cannot override this policy.\n\nSetting to \"Disabled\" sets media autoplay to \"Limit\". This limits websites that are allowed to autoplay media to webpages with high media engagement and active WebRTC streams. Prior to Microsoft Edge version 92, this would set media autoplay to \"Block\". Users cannot override this policy.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7658","uuid":"04b3870e-ca9a-4d87-ab00-df2448896f5d","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A7932029CA4C0954555C4780148CECB0AAD0BE8F\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'AutoplayAllowed must be set to disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235742","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235742","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235742","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235742r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235742","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000025","rule_title":"WebUSB must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the WebUSB API\" to enabled\" and select \"Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the WebUSB API\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Set whether websites can access connected USB devices. Access can be blocked completely or the user asked each time a website wants to get access to connected USB devices.\n\nOverride this policy for specific URL patterns by using the WebUsbAskForUrls and WebUsbBlockedForUrls policies.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, sites can ask users whether they can access the connected USB devices ('AskWebUsb') by default, and users can change this setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4864","uuid":"39a02383-e028-4efb-88fd-bab827546199","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3286FDCB1EC21D20A92C20599C9EBE25D1AF6298\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'WebUSB must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235743","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235743","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235743","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235743r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235743","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000026","rule_title":"Google Cast must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Cast/Enable Google Cast\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Cast/Enable Google Cast\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EnableMediaRouter\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enable this policy to enable Google Cast. Users will be able to launch it from the app menu, page context menus, media controls on Cast-enabled websites, and (if shown) the Cast toolbar icon.\n\nDisable this policy to disable Google Cast.\n\nBy default, Google Cast is enabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7239","uuid":"8a4d9749-3e30-49ad-b560-75d7b257bbba","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B68FF67EFB9BAA0ADB80013A3B969390826243AA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Google Cast must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235744","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235744","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235744","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235744r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235744","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000027","rule_title":"Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\" to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Control whether websites can access nearby Bluetooth devices. Access can be blocked completely or the site required to ask the user each time it wants to access a Bluetooth device.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, the default value ('AskWebBluetooth', meaning users are asked each time) is used and users can change it.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- BlockWebBluetooth (2) = Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API.\n- AskWebBluetooth (3) = Allow sites to ask the user to grant access to a nearby Bluetooth device.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6438","uuid":"b9082a2e-ba8d-483b-90e5-df79840d0620","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FF730238C66186BE8149F7B3389A405174194D84\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235745","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235745","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235745","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235745r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235745","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000028","rule_title":"Autofill for Credit Cards must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for credit cards\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for credit cards\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutofillCreditCardEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enables the Microsoft Edge AutoFill feature and lets users auto complete credit card information in web forms using previously stored information.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, AutoFill never suggests or fills credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that users might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can control AutoFill for credit cards.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8992","uuid":"466721a1-04c2-48a9-844d-88cda8520536","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 67F1C0F86AF55EB72D4570779D324FEB067F7F17\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Autofill for Credit Cards must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235746","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235746","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235746","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235746r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235746","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000029","rule_title":"Autofill for addresses must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for addresses\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for addresses\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutofillAddressEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enables the AutoFill feature and allows users to auto-complete address information in web forms using previously stored information.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, AutoFill never suggests or fills credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that users might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can control AutoFill for addresses in the user interface.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9054","uuid":"8530b317-7218-48ca-a5f6-bf10b0efa937","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C097F3F2DCCEEC1F23A887F1E9A61D62BD1C7049\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Autofill for addresses must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235747","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235747","title":"SRG-APP-000175","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235747","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","rule_id_src":"SV-235747r961038_rule","rule_id":"SV-235747","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000030","rule_title":"Online revocation checks must be performed.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EnableOnlineRevocationChecks\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If you enable this policy, Microsoft Edge will perform soft-fail, online OCSP/CRL checks. \"Soft fail\" means that if the revocation server can't be reached, the certificate will be considered valid.\n\nIf you disable the policy or don't configure it, Microsoft Edge won't perform online revocation checks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"3212","uuid":"57520561-b59f-414e-b17c-0e669f707f06","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2752F3309FC628C68FCA9BC9FE5B349736A4A63D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Online revocation checks must be performed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235748","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235748","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235748","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235748r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235748","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000031","rule_title":"Personalization of ads, search, and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow personalization of ads, search and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow personalization of ads, search and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PersonalizationReportingEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy prevents Microsoft from collecting a user's Microsoft Edge browsing history to be used for personalizing advertising, search, news and other Microsoft services.\n\nThis setting is only available for users with a Microsoft account. This setting is not available for child accounts or enterprise accounts.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot change or override the setting. If this policy is enabled or not configured, Microsoft Edge will default to the user's preference.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3367","uuid":"50df144e-9e42-4029-a16b-6f2b2ba8c9f2","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-235749","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235749","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235749","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235749r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235749","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000032","rule_title":"Site tracking of a user\u2019s location must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default geolocation setting\" to \"enabled\" and select \"Don't allow any site to track users' physical location\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default geolocation setting\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow any site to track users' physical location\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultGeolocationSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Set whether websites can track users' physical locations. Tracking can be allowed by default (\"AllowGeolocation\") or denied by default (\"BlockGeolocation\"), or the user can be asked each time a website requests their location (\"AskGeolocation\").\n\nIf this policy is not configured, \"AskGeolocation\" is used and the user can change it.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- AllowGeolocation (1) = Allow sites to track users' physical location.\n- BlockGeolocation (2) = Do not allow any site to track users' physical location.\n- AskGeolocation (3) = Ask whenever a site wants to track users' physical location.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2676","uuid":"c2735c4b-ea12-412c-b6f3-f91c219ec5e7","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 311F0AA842464E5188852318865D938DFC0D160F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Site tracking of a user\u2019s location must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235750","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235750","title":"SRG-APP-000080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235750","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","rule_id_src":"SV-235750r960864_rule","rule_id":"SV-235750","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000033","rule_title":"Browser history must be saved.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable deleting browser and download history\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable deleting browser and download history\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AllowDeletingBrowserHistory\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting disables deleting browser history and download history and prevents users from changing this setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000166"],"reference_identifier":"7987","uuid":"5a79b4ee-77a1-490b-89a7-d5a46e761e29","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 285CB666E001F99EC791FB3268B06892156E3BCC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Browser history must be saved.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235751","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235751","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235751","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235751r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235751","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000034","rule_title":"Edge development tools must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control where developer tools can be used\" to \"enabled\" and select \"Don't allow using the developer tools\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control where developer tools can be used\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow using the developer tools\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DeveloperToolsAvailability\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application-related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc., may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4067","uuid":"b0cbc190-64f3-486f-bd69-adcafb433a80","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 206BD43553F4640A9E1362AFB69117DB38A7FC7C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Edge development tools must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235752","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235752","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235752","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235752r1156563_rule","rule_id":"SV-235752","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000036","rule_title":"Download restrictions must be configured.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow download restrictions\" to \"Enabled\" and select one of the following: \"BlockDangerousDownloads\", \"Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads\", \"BlockAllDownloads\", or \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow download restrictions\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"BlockDangerousDownloads\", \"Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads\", or \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\". The more restrictive option, \"Block all downloads\", is also acceptable.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DownloadRestrictions\" is set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This configures the type of downloads that Microsoft Edge completely blocks without allowing users to override the security decision.\n\nSet \"BlockDangerousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of known dangerous downloads or that have dangerous file type extensions.\n\nSet \"BlockPotentiallyDangerousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads or that have dangerous file type extensions.\n\nSet \"BlockAllDownloads\" to block all downloads.\n\nSet \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of known malicious downloads.\n\nIf this policy is not configured or the \"DefaultDownloadSecurity\" option is not set, the downloads go through the usual security restrictions based on Microsoft Defender SmartScreen analysis results.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n\nDefaultDownloadSecurity (0) = No special restrictions\n\nBlockDangerousDownloads (1) = Block malicious downloads and dangerous file types\n\nBlockPotentiallyDangerousDownloads (2) = Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads and dangerous file types\n\nBlockAllDownloads (3) = Block all downloads\n\nBlockMaliciousDownloads (4) = Block malicious downloads","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4088","uuid":"6defebcd-87d8-4e92-be21-0739cd71cfa3","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3C5A236D3895D186CE8997F2B0092FC5A02E04FC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Download restrictions must be configured.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235753","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235753","title":"SRG-APP-000378","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235753","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000378","rule_id_src":"SV-235753r1015297_rule","rule_id":"SV-235753","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000039","rule_title":"URLs must be allowlisted for plugin use if used.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" to \"Enabled\". A list of allowlisted URLs may be specified here.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement for \"Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\n\"PopupsAllowedForUrls\" must be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PopupsAllowedForUrls\\1 = mydomain.com\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PopupsAllowedForUrls\\2 = myagency.mil\n\nIf configured, the list of domains for which Microsoft Edge allows pop-ups may be allowlisted.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Define a list of sites, based on URL patterns that can open pop-up windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"1301","uuid":"6cd1ac55-079b-4513-a4df-0e98e3ec08c8","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6DB1B82F716F05053EB34D55AACB0F7128BF7A9F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'URLs must be allowlisted for plugin use if used.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235754","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235754","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235754","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235754r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235754","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000041","rule_title":"Extensions installation must be blocklisted by default.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Control which extensions cannot be installed\" to \"Enabled\". A list of blocklisted extensions may then be specified.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Control which extensions cannot be installed\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist\\1\n\nIf the value for \"1\" is not set to \"REG_SZ = *\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"List specific extensions that users cannot install in Microsoft Edge. When this policy is deployed, any extensions on this list that were previously installed will be disabled, and the user will not be able to enable them. If an item is removed from the list of blocked extensions, the extension is automatically reenabled anywhere it was previously installed.\n\nUse \"*\" to block all extensions that are not explicitly listed in the allow list.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, users can install any extension in Microsoft Edge.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5844","uuid":"3d394cbf-d917-459b-b291-bb4eb205a2b0","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 938F4B13FA7D5ACAA10393948784688C7BB5B434\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Extensions installation must be blocklisted by default.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235755","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235755","title":"SRG-APP-000386","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235755","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000386","rule_id_src":"SV-235755r961479_rule","rule_id":"SV-235755","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000042","rule_title":"Extensions that are approved for use must be allowlisted if used.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Allow specific extensions to be installed\" to \"Enabled\".  A list of allowlisted extensions may then be specified.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement for \"Allow specific extensions to be installed\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Allow specific extensions to be installed\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\n\"ExtensionInstallAllowlist\" must be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\\1 = \"extension_id1\"\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\\2 = \"extension_id2\"\n\nIf configured, the list of extensions for which Microsoft Edge allows to be installed may be allowlisted.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"By default, all extensions are allowed. However, if all extensions are blocked by setting the \"ExtensionInstallBlockList\" policy to \"*,\" users can only install extensions defined in this policy.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001774"],"reference_identifier":"2569","uuid":"39fde0bd-8309-4829-84fc-5f3bd261dce5","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CEFFA09B984EB59F43E92D181A1DE73183785801\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Extensions that are approved for use must be allowlisted if used.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235756","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235756","title":"SRG-APP-000400","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235756","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000400","rule_id_src":"SV-235756r961521_rule","rule_id":"SV-235756","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000043","rule_title":"The Password Manager must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Password manager and protection/Enable saving passwords to the password manager\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Password manager and protection/Enable saving passwords to the password manager\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PasswordManagerEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enable Microsoft Edge to save user passwords.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, users can save their passwords in Microsoft Edge. The next time the user visits the site, Microsoft Edge will enter the password automatically.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002007"],"reference_identifier":"4571","uuid":"db21186e-65f3-4367-a7a8-8281323e3ab3","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8F9414CD1BA2C31C12F8C1727DAD6B4FD29A748D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Password Manager must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235758","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235758","title":"SRG-APP-000456","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235758","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","rule_id_src":"SV-235758r1117151_rule","rule_id":"SV-235758","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000045","rule_title":"The version of Microsoft Edge running on the system must be a supported version.","fix_text":"Install a supported version of Edge.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Cross-reference the build information displayed with the Microsoft Edge site to identify, at minimum, the oldest supported build available. \n\nIf the installed version of Edge is not supported by Microsoft, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously. \n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw). \n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications themselves that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means that the time period used must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may be dependent upon the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.\n\nThe application will be configured to check for and install security-relevant software updates within an identified time period from the availability of the update. The specific time period will be defined by an authoritative source (e.g., IAVM, CTOs, DTMs, and STIGs).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002605"],"reference_identifier":"8210","uuid":"c97088ee-08bd-4a65-a764-46b7c9afef0e","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2C552BB3765D70D25FB12F61BD7DB46C4322FFBB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The version of Microsoft Edge running on the system must be a supported version.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235760","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235760","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235760","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235760r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235760","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000047","rule_title":"Site isolation for every site must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable site isolation for every site\" to \"enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable site isolation for every site\" must be set to \"enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SitePerProcess\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"SitePerProcess\" policy can be used to prevent users from opting out of the default behavior of isolating all sites. The \"IsolateOrigins\" policy can be used to isolate additional, finer-grained origins.\n\nEnabling this policy prevents users from opting out of the default behavior where each site runs in its own process.\n\nIf this policy is not disabled or configured, a user can opt out of site isolation (e.g., by using \"Disable site isolation\" entry in edge://flags.) Disabling the policy or not configuring the policy does not turn off Site Isolation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9552","uuid":"bd3e08a8-0911-45db-8d65-d0c1ee2f29e4","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E57118CFCBC15E5394BDD9B761B465860CF0137A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Site isolation for every site must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235761","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235761","title":"SRG-APP-000142","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235761","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000142","rule_id_src":"SV-235761r1043177_rule","rule_id":"SV-235761","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000048","rule_title":"Supported authentication schemes must be configured.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/HTTP authentication/Supported authentication schemes\" to \"ntlm,negotiate\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/HTTP authentication/Supported authentication schemes\" must be set to  \"ntlm,negotiate\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AuthSchemes\" is not set to \"REG_SZ = ntlm,negotiate\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting specifies which HTTP authentication schemes are supported.\n\nThe policy can be configured by using these values: \"basic\", \"digest\", \"ntlm\", and \"negotiate\". Separate multiple values with commas.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, all four schemes are used.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000382"],"reference_identifier":"5894","uuid":"b8fe9c06-c73b-4246-b1ba-84a2cebab123","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 225E17D810EA9238F2061D0EB33554A417D448DD\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Supported authentication schemes must be configured.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235763","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235763","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235763","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235763r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235763","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000050","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SmartScreenEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures Microsoft Defender SmartScreen, which provides warning messages to help protect  users from potential phishing scams and malicious software. By default, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is disabled, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off.\n\nIf this setting is not configured, users can choose whether to use Microsoft Defender SmartScreen.\n\nThis policy is available only on Windows instances that are joined to a Microsoft Active Directory domain, Windows 10 Pro or Enterprise instances that enrolled for device management, or macOS instances that are that are managed via MDM or joined to a domain via MCX.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3968","uuid":"a180b02d-b478-4667-8a9d-9f6c6de25fc1","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FC987F607167C2DBE302AC70B51ED0BCCD831D7F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235764","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235764","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235764","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235764r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235764","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000051","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be configured to block potentially unwanted apps.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen to block potentially unwanted apps\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen to block potentially unwanted apps\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for SmartScreenPuaEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures blocking for potentially unwanted apps with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen. Potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen provides warning messages to help protect users from adware, coin miners, bundleware, and other low-reputation apps that are hosted by websites. Potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off by default.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is disabled, potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off.\n\nIf this setting is not configured, users can choose whether to use potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen.\n\nThis policy is available only on Windows instances that are joined to a Microsoft Active Directory domain, Windows 10 Pro or Enterprise instances that enrolled for device management, or macOS instances that are managed via MDM or joined to a domain via MCX.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8394","uuid":"7d1d4d10-d4ca-46f5-82a8-b1ce9830f930","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 36316DB3F2F8E6EB895B1D68D5D4D60B70A1604C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be configured to block potentially unwanted apps.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235765","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235765","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235765","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235765r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235765","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000052","rule_title":"The download location prompt must be configured.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Ask where to save downloaded files\" to \"enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Ask where to save downloaded files\" must be set to \"enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PromptForDownloadLocation\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting provides positive feedback before a download starts, limiting the possibility of inadvertent downloads without notifying the user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5681","uuid":"815681d0-9e96-4c86-9046-7a27fe9a24e7","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AC43BCA353F53FACBEDD8BCC9A51BCC91D9D2E02\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The download location prompt must be configured.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235766","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235766","title":"SRG-APP-000148","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235766","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000148","rule_id_src":"SV-235766r1051115_rule","rule_id":"SV-235766","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000054","rule_title":"Tracking of browsing activity must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Block tracking of users' web-browsing activity\" to \"Balanced\" or \"Strict\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Block tracking of users' web-browsing activity\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Balanced\" or \"Strict\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"TrackingPrevention\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\" or \"REG_DWORD = 3\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The setting allows websites to be blocked from tracking users' web-browsing activity.\n\nIf this policy is disabled or is not configured, users can set their own level of tracking prevention.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- TrackingPreventionOff (0) = Off (no tracking prevention)\n- TrackingPreventionBasic (1) = Basic (blocks harmful trackers; content and ads will be personalized)\n- TrackingPreventionBalanced (2) = Balanced (blocks harmful trackers and trackers from sites user has not visited; content and ads will be less personalized)\n- TrackingPreventionStrict (3) = Strict (blocks harmful trackers and majority of trackers from all sites; content and ads will have minimal personalization; some parts of sites might not work)","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000388"],"reference_identifier":"7857","uuid":"31be6f6d-4b81-4cb4-bd8b-50b77ab10ba3","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EE7A28A889036EC508BCE7AC032FE7077FDCBC47\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Tracking of browsing activity must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235767","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235767","title":"SRG-APP-000149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235767","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000149","rule_id_src":"SV-235767r960972_rule","rule_id":"SV-235767","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000055","rule_title":"A website's ability to query for payment methods must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow websites to query for available payment methods\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow websites to query for available payment methods\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for PaymentMethodQueryEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting determines whether websites can check if the user has payment methods saved.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, websites that use \"PaymentRequest.canMakePayment\" or \"PaymentRequest.hasEnrolledInstrument\" API will be informed that no payment methods are available.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or is not set, websites can check to determine if the user has payment methods saved.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2521","uuid":"3271c4b2-561e-47c8-af6d-0f42bde751ab","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A0147120AF17997CACA9F50D943C8BE532893F4B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'A website's ability to query for payment methods must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235768","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235768","title":"SRG-APP-000151","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235768","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000151","rule_id_src":"SV-235768r1015298_rule","rule_id":"SV-235768","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000056","rule_title":"Suggestions of similar web pages in the event of a navigation error must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for AlternateErrorPagesEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting allows Microsoft Edge to issue a connection to a web service to generate URL and search suggestions for connectivity issues such as DNS errors.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, a web service is used to generate URL and search suggestions for network errors.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, no calls to the web service are made and a standard error page is shown.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, Microsoft Edge respects the user preference that is set under Services at edge://settings/privacy. Specifically, there is a \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" toggle, which the user can switch on or off. \n\nNote that if this policy has been enabled (AlternateErrorPagesEnabled), the \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found setting\" is turned on, but the user cannot change the setting by using the toggle. \n\nIf this policy is disabled, the \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" setting is turned off, and the user cannot change the setting by using the toggle.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381","CCI-000767"],"reference_identifier":"7457","uuid":"e35a5dae-5573-45b0-b5d0-fc84f0009ff9","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 45BF0BD78749EB75FD58C8108E23BA4EF7409DA6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Suggestions of similar web pages in the event of a navigation error must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235769","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235769","title":"SRG-APP-000152","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235769","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000152","rule_id_src":"SV-235769r960981_rule","rule_id":"SV-235769","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000057","rule_title":"User feedback must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow user feedback\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow user feedback\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for UserFeedbackAllowed is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft Edge uses the Edge Feedback feature (enabled by default) to allow users to send feedback, suggestions, or customer surveys and to report any issues with the browser. By default, users cannot disable (turn off) the Edge Feedback feature.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can invoke Edge Feedback.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot invoke Edge Feedback.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6916","uuid":"9c30a012-9483-47eb-81fc-dd9b5df8979a","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4C6E1E85E6B68CDAFB858608B6818FE4F438B914\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User feedback must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235770","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235770","title":"SRG-APP-000153","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235770","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000153","rule_id_src":"SV-235770r960984_rule","rule_id":"SV-235770","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000058","rule_title":"The collections feature must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable the Collections feature\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable the Collections feature\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EdgeCollectionsEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting allows users to access the Collections feature, where they can collect, organize, share, and export content more efficiently and with Office integration.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can access and use the Collections feature in Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot access and use Collections in Microsoft Edge.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9133","uuid":"a3b5fc7f-d81e-416e-a09f-6569fd549368","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 121B0221BFC9C7EA8746E22BCED746483FF72649\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The collections feature must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235771","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235771","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235771","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235771r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235771","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000059","rule_title":"The Share Experience feature must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the Share experience\" to \"Don't allow using the Share experience\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the Share experience\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow using the Share experience\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ConfigureShare\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If this policy is set to \"ShareAllowed\" (the default), users will be able to access the Windows 10 Share experience from the Settings and More menu in Microsoft Edge to share with other apps on the system.\n\nIf this policy is set to \"ShareDisallowed\", users will not be able to access the Windows 10 Share experience. If the Share button is on the toolbar, it will also be hidden.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- ShareAllowed (0) = Allow using the Share experience.\n- ShareDisallowed (1) = Do not allow using the Share experience.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2851","uuid":"3966632e-ab74-4d12-808f-eabbee7ef79a","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AEFA06732E52D9A7D93CF663548CDE1F8352DF3D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Share Experience feature must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235772","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235772","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235772","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235772r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235772","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000060","rule_title":"Guest mode must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable guest mode\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable guest mode\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"BrowserGuestModeEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling Guest mode allows the use of guest profiles in Microsoft Edge. In a guest profile, the browser does not import browsing data from existing profiles, and it deletes browsing data when all guest profiles are closed.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, Microsoft Edge lets users browse in guest profiles.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, Microsoft Edge does not let users browse in guest profiles.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4114","uuid":"4f139511-848f-4700-86d6-522e4cae40db","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 354AEF3F779B0037939FB099EC1815DA7B996F19\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Guest mode must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235773","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235773","title":"SRG-APP-000156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235773","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000156","rule_id_src":"SV-235773r960993_rule","rule_id":"SV-235773","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000061","rule_title":"Relaunch notification must be required.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Notify a user that a browser restart is recommended or required for pending updates\" web-browsing activity to \"Required\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Notify a user that a browser restart is recommended or required for pending updates\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Required\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"RelaunchNotification\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users must be required to restart the browser to finish installation of pending updates and prevent users from continually using an old/vulnerable browser version.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6783","uuid":"d8ae6b6a-7611-4a44-9b0e-f4df20d914e0","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C7B52C7F3846577F231AE897F103B9612D323082\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Relaunch notification must be required.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235774","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235774","title":"SRG-APP-000157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235774","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000157","rule_id_src":"SV-235774r1015299_rule","rule_id":"SV-235774","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000062","rule_title":"The built-in DNS client must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Use built-in DNS client\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Use built-in DNS client\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"BuiltInDnsClientEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls whether to use the built-in DNS client.\n\nThis does not affect which DNS servers are used; it only controls the software stack that is used to communicate with them. For example, if the operating system is configured to use an enterprise DNS server, that same server would be used by the built-in DNS client. However, it is however possible that the built-in DNS client will address servers in different ways by using more modern DNS-related protocols such as DNS-over-TLS.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the built-in DNS client is used if it is available.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, the client is never used.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"reference_identifier":"3267","uuid":"a5a86d16-35fa-41da-8b47-ae17072d17ca","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 93E41D74AC9A60D61F9291150C6E31F774412BAF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The built-in DNS client must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-246736","group_tree":[{"id":"V-246736","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-246736","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-246736r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-246736","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000063","rule_title":"Use of the QUIC protocol must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow QUIC protocol\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow QUIC protocol\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"QuicAllowed\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"QUIC is used by more than half of all connections from the Edge web browser to Google's servers, and this activity is undesirable in the DoD.\n\nIf you enable this policy or don't configure it, the QUIC protocol is allowed.\n\nIf you disable this policy, the QUIC protocol is blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6088","uuid":"8505ca57-aa40-4df9-b156-0fbbcded20b6","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 62A24D95250D0109EADE05B4E691BA9934FCC489\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Use of the QUIC protocol must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251694","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251694","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251694","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251694r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251694","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000064","rule_title":"The list of domains media autoplay allows must be allowlisted if used.","fix_text":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay on specific sites\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThis requirement for \"AutoplayAllowlist\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay on specific sites\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nAutoplayAllowlist may be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutoplayAllowlist\\1 = mydomain.com\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutoplayAllowlist\\2 = myagency.mil\n\nIf configured, the list of domains for which autoplay is allowed may be allowlisted.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Define a list of sites, based on URL patterns, that are allowed to autoplay media.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, the global default value from the AutoplayAllowed policy (if set) or the user's personal configuration is used for all sites.\n\nEDGE-00-000024 disables the AutoplayAllowed policy.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5354","uuid":"03c6c6ad-0933-486f-8e5c-1b623eabf112","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B89ADD6D12F4F821FC74D467EDDA0F3075FE5171\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The list of domains media autoplay allows must be allowlisted if used.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-260465","group_tree":[{"id":"V-260465","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-260465","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-260465r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-260465","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000065","rule_title":"Visual Search must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Visual search enabled\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Visual search enabled\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"VisualSearchEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Visual Search allows for quick exploration of more related content about entities in an image.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, Visual Search will be enabled via image hover, context menu, and search in Sidebar.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, Visual Search will be disabled and more information about images will not be available via hover, context menu, and search in Sidebar.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2869","uuid":"34e1e5b7-2d71-4acd-a409-46ba6b0723f9","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 65371BD34B5B799531BD0FE457B7670B0645D026\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Visual Search must be disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-260466","group_tree":[{"id":"V-260466","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-260466","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-260466r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-260466","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000066","rule_title":"Copilot must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Show Hubs Sidebar\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Show Hubs Sidebar\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"HubsSidebarEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Sidebar is a launcher bar on the right side of Microsoft Edge's screen.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, the Sidebar will be shown. If this policy is disabled, the Sidebar will never be shown.\n\nDisabling Sidebar will disable Copilot.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9691","uuid":"6a9a96b7-b4c1-4b37-8497-96d482853b91","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C4C44A93DDBF848825400E837D9944B77BB53530\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Copilot must be disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-260467","group_tree":[{"id":"V-260467","title":"SRG-APP-000080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-260467","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","rule_id_src":"SV-260467r960864_rule","rule_id":"SV-260467","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000067","rule_title":"Session only-based cookies must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Configure cookies\" to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Keep cookies for the duration of the session, except ones listed in 'SaveCookiesOnExit'\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Configure cookies\" is set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Keep cookies for the duration of the session, except ones listed in 'SaveCookiesOnExit'\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \u201cDefaultCookiesSetting\u201d is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 4\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Cookies must only be allowed per session and only for approved URLs as permanently stored cookies can be used for malicious intent. \n\nApproved URLs may be allowlisted via the \"CookiesAllowedForUrls\" or \"SaveCookiesOnExit\" policy settings, but these are not requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000166"],"reference_identifier":"2490","uuid":"bb8b28b5-46e6-43af-a104-fa2bb70ff491","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8BD5892888C9E44AED08F2643A38BF94997989E0\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Session only-based cookies must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-266981","group_tree":[{"id":"V-266981","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-266981","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-266981r1169858_rule","rule_id":"SV-266981","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000068","rule_title":"FriendlyURLs must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft EdgeConfigure the default paste format of URLs copied from Microsoft Edge, and determine if additional formats will be available to users\" to \"enabled\" and select \"The plain URL without any extra information, such as the page\u00b4s title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\"","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the default paste format of URLs copied from Microsoft Edge and determine if additional formats will be available to users\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"The plain URL without any extra information, such as the page\u00b4s title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ConfigureFriendlyURLFormat\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If FriendlyURLs are enabled, Microsoft Edge will compute additional representations of the URL and place them on the clipboard.\n\nThis policy configures what format will be pasted when the user pastes in external applications, or inside Microsoft Edge without the \"Paste As\" context menu item.\n\nIf configured, this policy makes a choice on behalf of the user. The options in edge://settings/shareCopyPaste will be grayed out, and the options in the \"Paste As\" context menu will not be available.\n\nNot configured = The user will be able to choose their preferred paste format. By default, this is set to the friendly URL format. The \"Paste As\" menu will be available in Microsoft Edge.\n\n1 = No additional formats will be stored on the clipboard. There will be no \"Paste as\" context menu item in Microsoft Edge and the only format available to paste will be the plain text URL format. Effectively, the friendly URL feature will be disabled.\n\n3 = The user will get a friendly URL whenever they paste into surfaces that accept rich text. The plain URL will still be available for non-rich surfaces. There will be no \"Paste As\" menu in Microsoft Edge.\n\n4 = (Not currently used)\n\nThe richer formats may not be well-supported in some paste destinations and/or websites. In these scenarios, the plain URL option is recommended when configuring this policy.\n\nThe recommended policy is available in Microsoft Edge 105 or later.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n\nPlainText (1) = The plain URL without any extra information, such as the page's title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\n\nTitledHyperlink (3) = Titled Hyperlink: A hyperlink that points to the copied URL, but whose visible text is the title of the destination page. This is the Friendly URL format.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1513","uuid":"41c8d6e0-02ec-46bd-8716-9f8f0d4a49c1","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 21C09B9EC1D5DAF673C8D19A8A87A1797C1C4ADF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'FriendlyURLs must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-279940","group_tree":[{"id":"V-279940","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-279940","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-279940r1156561_rule","rule_id":"SV-279940","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000069","rule_title":"Access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Control access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance in Microsoft Edge for Business\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance in Microsoft Edge for Business\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ComposeInlineEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy controls whether users can use writing support features in Microsoft Edge for Business, such as Rewrite, which utilizes Microsoft 365 Copilot Chat.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9108","uuid":"750a7da1-9dd5-426d-8d7f-11bca5f58a6e","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 605014A1B715D84D04B89A2D8AABB28CC3F378A4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-283439","group_tree":[{"id":"V-283439","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-283439","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-283439r1192850_rule","rule_id":"SV-283439","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000070","rule_title":"Spell checking provided by Microsoft Editor must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Spell checking provided by Microsoft Editor\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Spell checking provided by Microsoft Editor\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for MicrosoftEditorProofingEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Microsoft Editor service provides enhanced spell and grammar checking for editable text fields on web pages.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or incorrectly configured, Microsoft Editor spell check can be used for eligible text fields.\n\nIf you disable this policy, spell check can only be provided by local engines that use platform or Hunspell services. The results from these engines might be less informative than the results Microsoft Editor can provide.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6537","uuid":"7c095949-ca80-437f-a99b-b67e3ab377cc","stig_uuid":"c3c6a856-1d48-4b3a-8fdb-01739a15bada","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""}]},{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-23T17:12:42.0000000+00:00","module":{"name":"Scan-DefenderAV_Checks","version":"1.2604.2"}},"stig_name":"Microsoft Defender Antivirus Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Microsoft Defender Antivirus","stig_id":"MS_Defender_Antivirus","release_info":"Release: 8 Benchmark Date: 01 Apr 2026","version":"2","uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","reference_identifier":"5114","size":67,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-213426","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213426","title":"SRG-APP-000279","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213426","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-APP-000279","rule_id_src":"SV-213426r961197_rule","rule_id":"SV-213426","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000001","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block the Potentially Unwanted Application (PUA) feature.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> \"Configure Detection for Potentially Unwanted Applications\" to \"Enabled\" and \"Block\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> \"Configure detection for potentially unwanted applications\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Block\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nIf the value \"PUAProtection\" does not exist, this is a finding.\n\nIf the value \"PUAProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"After enabling this feature, PUA protection blocking takes effect on endpoint clients after the next signature update or computer restart. Signature updates take place daily under typical circumstances. PUA will be blocked and automatically quarantined.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89827","V-75147","CCI-001243"],"reference_identifier":"5473","uuid":"62353c41-a922-419f-8c46-64ba43a5bd40","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 47A49DC6587186BBB499D8ACC76616D1B1857FC1\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block the Potentially Unwanted Application (PUA) feature.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213427","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213427","title":"SRG-APP-000279","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213427","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000279","rule_id_src":"SV-213427r961197_rule","rule_id":"SV-213427","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000003","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to automatically take action on all detected tasks.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> \"Turn off routine remediation\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> \"Turn off routine remediation\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableRoutinelyTakingAction\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows Microsoft Defender configuration to automatically take action on all detected threats. The action to be taken on a particular threat is determined by the combination of the policy-defined action user-defined action and the signature-defined action. If this policy setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender does not automatically take action on the detected threats but prompts users to choose from the actions available for each threat. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, Microsoft Defender automatically takes action on all detected threats after a nonconfigurable delay of approximately five seconds.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89831","V-75151","CCI-001243"],"reference_identifier":"9893","uuid":"66adb96d-43a3-41ee-a5a6-65209373e1aa","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5E9981DD106C8D6CF1BD802DEC1270D550656BE2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to automatically take action on all detected tasks.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213428","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213428","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213428","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-213428r1190706_rule","rule_id":"SV-213428","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000004","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to run and scan for malware and other potentially unwanted software.","fix_text":"For Windows 10: Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus \"Turn off Microsoft Defender Antivirus\" to \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> \"Turn off Windows Defender Antivirus\" is set to \u201cNot Configured\u201d.\n\nFor Windows 10:\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableAntiSpyware\" does not exist, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting turns off Microsoft Defender Antivirus. If this policy setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender Antivirus does not run and computers are not scanned for malware or other potentially unwanted software. \n\nWhen the setting is disabled and a third-party antivirus solution is installed, the two applications can both simultaneously try to protect the system. The two AV solutions both attempt to quarantine the same threat and will fight for access to delete the file. Users will see conflicts and the system may lock up until the two solutions finish processing. \n\nWhen the setting is not configured and a third-party antivirus solution is installed, both applications coexist on the system without conflicts. Defender Antivirus will automatically disable itself and will enable if the third-party solution stops functioning. When the setting is not configured and Defender Antivirus is the only AV solution, Defender AV will run (default state) and receive definition updates. An administrator account is needed to turn off the service. A standard user cannot disable the service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89833","V-75153","CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"4941","uuid":"a6dceb69-81ce-4909-b656-e68ece7ec418","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7C382B95356670A2E16C49E7F423747728C58BCC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to run and scan for malware and other potentially unwanted software.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213429","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213429","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213429","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-213429r1190707_rule","rule_id":"SV-213429","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000005","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not exclude files for scanning.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Exclusions >> \"Path Exclusions\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Exclusions >> \"Path Exclusions\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured.\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Exclusions\n \nCriteria: If the value \"Exclusions_Paths\" does not exist, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows disabling of scheduled and real-time scanning for files under the paths specified or for the fully qualified resources specified. Paths should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair where the name should be a string representation of a path or a fully qualified resource name. As an example, a path might be defined as: \"c:\\Windows\" to exclude all files in this directory. A fully qualified resource name might be defined as: \"C:\\Windows\\App.exe\". The value is not used and it is recommended that this be set to 0.\n\nExceptions can be made to allow file/folders that are impacting enterprise applications to be excluded from being scanned. All exclusions should be documented and approved.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89835","V-75155","CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"6407","uuid":"2f04fd32-51f6-4e6a-b65e-b6c69f6fb037","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 09DA1A1677FB6C4924FEABC46218021C792A36CE\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not exclude files for scanning.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213430","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213430","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213430","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-213430r1190710_rule","rule_id":"SV-213430","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000006","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not exclude files opened by specified processes.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Exclusions >> \"Process Exclusions\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Exclusions >> \"Process Exclusions\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Exclusions\n\nCriteria: If the value \"Exclusions_Processes\" does not exist, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the disabling of scheduled and real-time scanning for any file opened by any of the specified processes. The process itself will not be excluded. To exclude the process, use the Path exclusion. Processes should be added under the options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair where the name should be a string representation of the path to the process image. Note that only executables can be excluded. For example, a process might be defined as: \"c:\\windows\\app.exe\". The value is not used and it is recommended that this be set to 0.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89837","V-75157","CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3658","uuid":"bc038912-3c9a-495b-b4b1-451ee5dc50ba","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4118523A08770BFE4BA552B62C2B2233E9F81058\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not exclude files opened by specified processes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213431","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213431","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213431","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-213431r1190712_rule","rule_id":"SV-213431","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000007","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to enable the Automatic Exclusions feature.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Exclusions >> \"Turn off Auto Exclusions\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Exclusions >> \"Turn off Auto Exclusions\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Exclusions\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableAutoExclusions\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting allows an administrator to specify if Automatic Exclusions feature for Server SKUs should be turned off.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89839","V-75159","CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"1081","uuid":"c1cffe79-9727-4943-b389-158a96976acc","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 43784274B59D8185F6BF3A5AC637B87AC1040795\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to enable the Automatic Exclusions feature.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213432","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213432","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213432","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213432r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213432","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000008","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to disable local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS.","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Configure local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Configure local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n     \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideSpynetReporting\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration to join Microsoft MAPS. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89841","V-75161","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3093","uuid":"93fac073-031c-43d5-bfa5-46a1f25ecbe3","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 77AF26D5CA45DAAF314A7099C5CEF46DA1F35254\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to disable local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213433","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213433","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213433","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-213433r1190715_rule","rule_id":"SV-213433","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000009","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to check in real time with MAPS before content is run or accessed.","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Configure the 'Block at First Sight' feature\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Configure the 'Block at First Sight' feature\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableBlockAtFirstSeen\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This feature ensures the device checks in real time with the Microsoft Active Protection Service (MAPS) before allowing certain content to be run or accessed. If this feature is disabled, the check will not occur, which will lower the protection state of the device. \n\nEnabled - The Block at First Sight setting is turned on. \nDisabled - The Block at First Sight setting is turned off. \n\nThis feature requires these Group Policy settings to be set as follows: \nMAPS >> The \"Join Microsoft MAPS\" must be enabled or the \"Block at First Sight\" feature will not function. \nMAPS >> The \"Send file samples when further analysis is required\" should be set to 1 (Send safe samples) or 3 (Send all samples). Setting to 0 (Always Prompt) will lower the protection state of the device. Setting to 2 (Never send) means the \"Block at First Sight\" feature will not function. \nReal-time Protection >> The \"Scan all downloaded files and attachments\" policy must be enabled or the \"Block at First Sight\" feature will not function. \nReal-time Protection >> Do not enable the \"Turn off real-time protection\" policy or the \"Block at First Sight\" feature will not function.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89843","V-75163","CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"1106","uuid":"201d4e22-12df-4f5b-b8e6-6678cfa849b3","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 559A95D9176907FDDBF4612685DC342907441C46\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to check in real time with MAPS before content is run or accessed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213434","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213434","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213434","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213434r1134051_rule","rule_id":"SV-213434","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000010","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must join Microsoft MAPS.","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is Not Applicable.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Join Microsoft MAPS\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Basic MAPS\" or \"Advanced MAPS\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems, this is Not Applicable.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Join Microsoft MAPS\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Advanced MAPS\" is selected from the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\n\nCriteria: If the value \"SpynetReporting\" is REG_DWORD = 1, or REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows joining Microsoft MAPS. Microsoft MAPS is the online community that helps in choosing how to respond to potential threats. The community also helps stop the spread of new malicious software infections. You can choose to send basic or additional information about detected software. Additional information helps Microsoft create new definitions and protect your computer. This information can include things like location of detected items on your computer if harmful software was removed. The information will be automatically collected and sent. In some instances personal information might unintentionally be sent to Microsoft. However Microsoft will not use this information to identify you or contact you. \n\nPossible options are: \n(0x0) Disabled (default) \n(0x1) Basic membership \n(0x2) Advanced membership \n\nBasic membership will send basic information to Microsoft about software that has been detected, including where the software came from, the actions that you apply or that are applied automatically, and whether the actions were successful. Advanced membership will send, in addition to basic information, more information to Microsoft about malicious software spyware and potentially unwanted software, including the location of the software file names, how the software operates, and how it has impacted your computer. \n\nIf this setting is enabled, you will join Microsoft MAPS with the membership specified. If this setting is disabled or do not configured, you will not join Microsoft MAPS. In Windows 10, Basic membership is no longer available, so setting the value to 1 or 2 enrolls the device into Advanced membership.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89847","V-75167","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"7343","uuid":"28142389-63f4-4538-bbf9-a9d2cb1843d6","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 002201DA06AC3FC2E8A4682BCDA507658D2F8C96\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Microsoft Defender AV must join Microsoft MAPS.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213435","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213435","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213435","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213435r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213435","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000011","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to only send safe samples for MAPS telemetry.","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Send file samples when further analysis is required\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Send safe samples\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Send file samples when further analysis is required\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Send safe samples\" is selected from the drop-down box.\n     \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\n\nCriteria: If the value \"SubmitSamplesConsent\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures behavior of samples submission when opt-in for MAPS telemetry is set. Possible options are:  \n(0x0) Always prompt\n(0x1) Send safe samples automatically \n(0x2) Never send  \n(0x3) Send all samples automatically","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89887","V-75207","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4167","uuid":"20f26dfb-8767-477f-92bc-69169bd2748d","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BD4B18954DB9C0AABDD9FC79DE0A2003A15292C4\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to only send safe samples for MAPS telemetry.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213436","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213436","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213436","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-213436r1190716_rule","rule_id":"SV-213436","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000012","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for protocol recognition for network protection.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Network Inspection System >> \"Turn on protocol recognition\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Network Inspection System >> \"Turn on protocol recognition\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableProtocolRecognition\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of protocol recognition for network protection against exploits of known vulnerabilities. If this setting is enabled or not configured, protocol recognition will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, protocol recognition will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89889","V-75209","CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"5741","uuid":"5f97b3df-0802-460c-87a1-e40f880c5be9","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A00EC0A493EE502898E6264DECB20CC84EE7C4DE\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for protocol recognition for network protection.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213437","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213437","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213437","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","rule_id_src":"SV-213437r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-213437","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000013","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow local override of monitoring for file and program activity.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for monitoring file and program activity on your computer\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for monitoring file and program activity on your computer\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideDisableOnAccessProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration of monitoring for file and program activity on your computer. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89891","V-75211","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"3298","uuid":"3a90ddb1-f713-4c9e-ab7c-234ad594cd94","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EBACB61F740900CD0BA57009FE39CF4BD23A4774\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow local override of monitoring for file and program activity.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213438","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213438","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213438","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","rule_id_src":"SV-213438r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-213438","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000014","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideRealtimeScanDirection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration of monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89893","V-75213","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"1855","uuid":"ea3e02eb-a497-43c3-be42-1e0f1807eae4","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-213439","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213439","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213439","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","rule_id_src":"SV-213439r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-213439","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000015","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of scanning for downloaded files and attachments.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for scanning all downloaded files and attachments\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for scanning all downloaded files and attachments\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideDisableIOAVProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration of scanning for all downloaded files and attachments. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89895","V-75215","CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"8399","uuid":"a4c5f294-9811-4fe8-81ba-5e8f0fb139d9","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2802C05DD62A878D47B2D384DFD39CF33D79672F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of scanning for downloaded files and attachments.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213440","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213440","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213440","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213440r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213440","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000016","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of behavior monitoring.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for turn on behavior monitoring\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for turn on behavior monitoring\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideDisableBehaviorMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration of behavior monitoring. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89897","V-75217","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4543","uuid":"edf26e76-ec58-4d00-9410-365ef4c21f64","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EF1A967F73E0C4AEF4F59D4D9788B1C2C5BB6639\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of behavior monitoring.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213441","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213441","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213441","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-213441r1190717_rule","rule_id":"SV-213441","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000017","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV Group Policy settings must take priority over the local preference settings.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override to turn on real-time protection\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override to turn on real-time protection\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideDisableRealtimeMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration to turn on real-time protection. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89899","V-75219","CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"2726","uuid":"2c6b94d6-074c-4235-a6f0-29bcdd728ee2","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AB4B6F31D8D64A91F6E00541E21304B846481AA2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV Group Policy settings must take priority over the local preference settings.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213442","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213442","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213442","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-213442r1190718_rule","rule_id":"SV-213442","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000018","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must monitor for incoming and outgoing files.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure monitoring for incoming and outgoing file and program activity\" to \"Enabled\" with a policy option value of \"bi-directional (full on-access)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure monitoring for incoming and outgoing file and program activity\" is set to \"Enabled\" with a policy option value of \"bi-directional (full on-access)\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"RealtimeScanDirection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1 or 2, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of monitoring for incoming and outgoing files without having to turn off monitoring entirely. It is recommended for use on servers that have a lot of incoming and outgoing file activity but for performance reasons need to have scanning disabled for a particular scan direction. The appropriate configuration should be evaluated based on the server role. Note that this configuration is only honored for NTFS volumes. For any other file system type, full monitoring of file and program activity will be present on those volumes. \n\nThe options for this setting are mutually exclusive: \n0 = Scan incoming and outgoing files (default) \n1 = Scan incoming files only \n2 = Scan outgoing files only \n\nAny other value, or if the value does not exist, resolves to the default (0). If this setting is enabled, the specified type of monitoring will be enabled. If this setting is disabled or not configured, monitoring for incoming and outgoing files will be enabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89901","V-75221","CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"1039","uuid":"472e36b2-2d4b-4db0-a68c-6968b52751d5","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 75BC628240AF408381DEF580A98168A54C433879\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must monitor for incoming and outgoing files.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213443","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213443","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213443","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-213443r1190719_rule","rule_id":"SV-213443","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000019","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to monitor for file and program activity.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Monitor file and program activity on your computer\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Monitor file and program activity on your computer to be scanned\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableOnAccessProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows configuration of monitoring for file and program activity. If this setting is enabled or not configured, monitoring for file and program activity will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, monitoring for file and program activity will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89903","V-75223","CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"6860","uuid":"d3d17b41-cdcb-43f3-bbed-2bc21dd1858f","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-213444","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213444","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213444","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","rule_id_src":"SV-213444r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-213444","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000020","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan all downloaded files and attachments.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Scan all downloaded files and attachments\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Scan all downloaded files and attachments\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableIOAVProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows configuration of scanning for all downloaded files and attachments. If this setting is enabled or not configured, scanning for all downloaded files and attachments will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, scanning for all downloaded files and attachments will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89905","V-75225","CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"1590","uuid":"35946736-b9dc-4c04-b4cd-fc3e7132069e","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8BFD2AF8DCB1D4A06F2AEADF5DC14C51E4895ADC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan all downloaded files and attachments.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213445","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213445","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213445","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-213445r1190720_rule","rule_id":"SV-213445","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000021","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to always enable real-time protection.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Turn off real-time protection\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Turn off real-time protection\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableRealtimeMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting turns off real-time protection prompts for known malware detection. Microsoft Defender Antivirus alerts when malware or potentially unwanted software attempts to install itself or to run on a user's computer. If this policy setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender Antivirus will not prompt users to take actions on malware detections. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, Microsoft Defender Antivirus will prompt users to take actions on malware detections.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89907","V-75227","CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"1518","uuid":"866fa5af-78ba-4495-9252-98a474059cc4","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D797AD79939EEB0347C611BF5926B14ED9D3806B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to always enable real-time protection.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213446","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213446","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213446","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213446r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213446","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000022","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to enable behavior monitoring.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Turn on behavior monitoring\" to \"Enabled \" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Turn on behavior monitoring\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableBehaviorMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows configuration of behavior monitoring. If this setting is enabled or not configured, behavior monitoring will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, behavior monitoring will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89909","V-75229","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"8054","uuid":"dcc73449-018a-4c31-8f2e-3b0e6fab7f44","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D69CF1A429838B7BB6D3D369DA5C2388181F241C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to enable behavior monitoring.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213447","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213447","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213447","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-213447r1190721_rule","rule_id":"SV-213447","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000023","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to process scanning when real-time protection is enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Turn on process scanning whenever real-time protection is enabled\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Turn on process scanning whenever real-time protection is enabled\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableScanOnRealtimeEnable\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of process scanning when real-time protection is turned on. This helps to catch malware, which could start when real-time protection is turned off. If this setting is enabled or not configured, a process scan will be initiated when real-time protection is turned on. If this setting is disabled, a process scan will not be initiated when real-time protection is turned on.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89911","V-75231","CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"8136","uuid":"2577fa29-f061-46fb-80fc-3b870bcc90ad","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EF62511D62CCDE4972B9190E388179F92754367B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to process scanning when real-time protection is enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213448","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213448","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213448","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-213448r1190722_rule","rule_id":"SV-213448","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000024","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan archive files.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Scan archive files\" to \"Enabled \" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Scan archive files\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableArchiveScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of scans for malicious software and unwanted software in archive files such as .ZIP or .CAB files. If this setting is enabled or not configured, archive files will be scanned. If this setting is disabled, archive files will not be scanned.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89913","V-75233","CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3827","uuid":"31ebf6bd-971f-48a1-aec7-bde4d6b7f4f2","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8FA72040155D4679429067BF1813C0A5EFC9618A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan archive files.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213449","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213449","title":"SRG-APP-000073","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213449","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000073","rule_id_src":"SV-213449r960852_rule","rule_id":"SV-213449","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000025","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan removable drives.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Scan removable drives\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Scan removable drives\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableRemovableDriveScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether or not to scan for malicious software and unwanted software in the contents of removable drives such as USB flash drives when running a full scan. If this setting is enabled, removable drives will be scanned during any type of scan. If this setting is disabled or not configured, removable drives will not be scanned during a full scan. Removable drives may still be scanned during quick scan and custom scan.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89915","V-75235","CCI-000870"],"reference_identifier":"5856","uuid":"e81b0a6d-258f-4e22-970d-e459b3504f51","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BE8A824E24AFD5A7E7E18FD9C53A48FBB4ACFEA3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan removable drives.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213450","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213450","title":"SRG-APP-000277","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213450","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000277","rule_id_src":"SV-213450r961191_rule","rule_id":"SV-213450","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000026","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to perform a weekly scheduled scan.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Specify the day of the week to run a scheduled scan\" to \"Enabled \" and select anything other than \"Never\" in the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Specify the day of the week to run a scheduled scan\" is set to \"Enabled\" and anything other than \"Never\" is selected in the drop-down box.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"ScheduleDay\" is REG_DWORD = 0x8, this is a finding.\n\nValues of 0x0 through 0x7 are acceptable and not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows specifying the day of the week on which to perform a scheduled scan. The scan can also be configured to run every day or to never run at all. This setting can be configured with the following ordinal number values: \n(0x0) Every Day  \n(0x1) Sunday  \n(0x2) Monday  \n(0x3) Tuesday  \n(0x4) Wednesday  \n(0x5) Thursday  \n(0x6) Friday  \n(0x7) Saturday  \n(0x8) Never (default)  \n\nIf this setting is enabled, a scheduled scan will run at the frequency specified. If this setting is disabled or not configured, a scheduled scan will run at a default frequency.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89917","V-75237","CCI-001241"],"reference_identifier":"1369","uuid":"71a386e4-1b7b-46a1-92ff-8954926c2822","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2D4391B84342E498DF1A97164554B7AA8889E071\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to perform a weekly scheduled scan.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213451","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213451","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213451","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213451r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213451","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000027","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to turn on e-mail scanning.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Turn on e-mail scanning\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Turn on e-mail scanning\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableEmailScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of e-mail scanning. When e-mail scanning is enabled, the engine will parse the mailbox and mail files according to their specific format in order to analyze the mail bodies and attachments. Several e-mail formats are currently supported, for example: pst (Outlook), dbx mbx mime (Outlook Express), binhex (Mac). If this setting is enabled, e-mail scanning will be enabled. If this setting is disabled or not configured, e-mail scanning will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89919","V-75239","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4316","uuid":"8b624dc1-c70c-4be4-a117-7f78e2cabb1f","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 77B8BAE596B26560F503C8B0C2E338F99C64D5D3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to turn on e-mail scanning.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213452","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213452","title":"SRG-APP-000276","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213452","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-APP-000276","rule_id_src":"SV-213452r1190723_rule","rule_id":"SV-213452","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000028","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV spyware definition age must not exceed 7 days.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender Antivirus >> Signature Updates >> \"Define the number of days before spyware definitions are considered out of date\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"7\" or less in the drop-down box.\n\nDo not select a value of 0. This disables the option.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Security Intelligence Updates >> \"Define the number of days before spyware security intelligence considered out of date\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"7\" or less is selected in the drop-down box (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).\n\nIf third-party antispyware is installed and up to date, the Windows Defender AV spyware age requirement will be NA.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\n\nCriteria: If the value \"ASSignatureDue\" is REG_DWORD = 7, this is not a finding.\n\nA value of 1 - 6 is also acceptable and not a finding.\n\nA value of 0 is a finding.\n\nA value higher than 7 is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows defining the number of days that must pass before spyware definitions are considered out of date. If definitions are determined to be out of date, this state may trigger several additional actions, including falling back to an alternative update source or displaying a warning icon in the user interface. By default this value is set to 14 days. \n\nIf this setting is enabled, spyware definitions will be considered out of date after the number of days specified have passed without an update. If this setting is disabled or not configured, spyware definitions will be considered out of date after the default number of days have passed without an update.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89921","V-75241","CCI-004964"],"reference_identifier":"2459","uuid":"68466756-e5b3-42ee-9c01-7b094ac1c2a3","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BC8CC783D1B3B494008889FAA7E391520C9BB98C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV spyware definition age must not exceed 7 days.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213453","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213453","title":"SRG-APP-000276","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213453","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-APP-000276","rule_id_src":"SV-213453r1190724_rule","rule_id":"SV-213453","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000029","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV virus definition age must not exceed 7 days.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Signature Updates >> \"Define the number of days before virus definitions are considered out of date\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"7\" or less in the drop-down box.\n\nDo not select a value of 0. This disables the option.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >>Security Intelligence Updates >> \"Define the number of days before virus security intelligence considered out of date\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"7\" or less is selected in the drop-down box (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).\n\nIf third-party antivirus protection is installed and up to date, the Windows Defender Antivirus age requirement is NA.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\n\nCriteria: If the value \"AVSignatureDue\" is REG_DWORD = 7, this is not a finding.\n\nA value of 1 - 6 is also acceptable and not a finding.\n\nA value of 0 is a finding.\n\nA value higher than 7 is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows defining the number of days that must pass before virus definitions are considered out of date. If definitions are determined to be out of date, this state may trigger several additional actions, including falling back to an alternative update source or displaying a warning icon in the user interface. By default, this value is set to 14 days. \n\nIf this setting is enabled, virus definitions will be considered out of date after the number of days specified have passed without an update. If this setting is disabled or not configured, virus definitions will be considered out of date after the default number of days have passed without an update.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89923","V-75243","CCI-004964"],"reference_identifier":"3437","uuid":"f5e80c64-633d-4ccd-8987-3ceb3762a26d","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 08AFE02B169408D08F479F62C0AFC3D4333C7504\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV virus definition age must not exceed 7 days.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213454","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213454","title":"SRG-APP-000261","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213454","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000261","rule_id_src":"SV-213454r961161_rule","rule_id":"SV-213454","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000030","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to check for definition updates daily.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Signature Updates >> \"Specify the day of the week to check for definition updates\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Every Day\" in the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Security Intelligence Updates >> \"Specify the day of the week to check for security intelligence updates\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Every Day\" is selected in the drop-down box.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\n\nCriteria: If the value \"ScheduleDay\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows specifying the day of the week on which to check for definition updates. The check can also be configured to run every day or to never run at all. This setting can be configured with the following ordinal number values: \n(0x0) Every Day (default)  \n(0x1) Sunday   \n(0x2) Monday  \n(0x3) Tuesday  \n(0x4) Wednesday  \n(0x5) Thursday  \n(0x6) Friday  \n(0x7) Saturday  \n(0x8) Never  \n\nIf this setting is enabled, the check for definition updates will occur at the frequency specified. If this setting is disabled or not configured, the check for definition updates will occur at a default frequency.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89925","V-75245","CCI-001308"],"reference_identifier":"5773","uuid":"65b85ae8-bf98-4ae7-8bab-736ea7a5f8a4","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7AB099BBFC45023485F26B4CE9B722D7AFB7FB0E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to check for definition updates daily.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213455","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213455","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213455","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-213455r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-213455","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000031","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Severe.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nSelect the \"Show\u2026\" option box and enter \"5\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\".  \n\nClick the \u201cShow\u2026\u201d box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"5\" and the \"Value\" field  contains \"2\".  A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"5\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High  \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89927","V-75247","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"8073","uuid":"52b99bad-3fbf-47c9-8ce4-b464e96cad80","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DB6FCD914F69416A314836004E44916709FC085A\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Severe.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213456","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213456","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213456","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213456r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213456","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000032","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block executable content from email client and webmail.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\u201d.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This rule blocks the following file types from being run or launched from an email seen in either Microsoft Outlook or webmail (such as Gmail.com or Outlook.com):\nExecutable files (such as .exe, .dll, or .scr)\nScript files (such as a PowerShell .ps, VisualBasic .vbs, or JavaScript .js file)\nScript archive files","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-92661","V-77965","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"7275","uuid":"8fd4611a-20ff-4f95-bd26-380e0c7fa9ec","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 79A32B5843E135DD940B6E121D50825EB5BC9BAD\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block executable content from email client and webmail.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213457","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213457","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213457","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213457r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213457","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000033","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured block Office applications from creating child processes.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\u201d.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Office apps, such as Word or Excel, will not be allowed to create child processes. This is a typical malware behavior, especially for macro-based attacks that attempt to use Office apps to launch or download malicious executables.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-92663","V-77967","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"1173","uuid":"83afc3f3-711e-4475-a81d-8a83b74c7447","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 10CDD6088D3A8A04208F039AB2B1FF60B0609BC7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured block Office applications from creating child processes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213458","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213458","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213458","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213458r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213458","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000034","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured block Office applications from creating executable content.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\u201d.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899\nValue:  1\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This rule targets typical behaviors used by suspicious and malicious add-ons and scripts (extensions) that create or launch executable files. This is a typical malware technique. Extensions will be blocked from being used by Office apps. Typically these extensions use the Windows Scripting Host (.wsh files) to run scripts that automate certain tasks or provide user-created add-on features.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-92665","V-77969","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"8822","uuid":"b5c7822c-4786-4fb7-b2e5-06cc4c285da7","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8A6F4DA591F3B58B6A57864CD0B119E3A3B4ACFA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured block Office applications from creating executable content.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213459","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213459","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213459","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213459r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213459","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000035","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block Office applications from injecting into other processes.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\u201d.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Office apps, such as Word, Excel, or PowerPoint, will not be able to inject code into other processes. This is typically used by malware to run malicious code in an attempt to hide the activity from antivirus scanning engines.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-92667","V-77971","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"8848","uuid":"82c65110-2ec0-4017-8a26-0fffce9114ec","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0E3FF03C9028EC2B61A5C21E464D5322A8BAB70C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block Office applications from injecting into other processes.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213460","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213460","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213460","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213460r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213460","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000036","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to impede JavaScript and VBScript to launch executables.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\". Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D \nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"JavaScript and VBScript scripts can be used by malware to launch other malicious apps. This rule prevents these scripts from being allowed to launch apps, thus preventing malicious use of the scripts to spread malware and infect machines.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-92669","V-77973","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"8750","uuid":"f160a378-b548-41b1-9074-1174e92f466c","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4517613AAA87009F4A26FDC99606B4D20A36E653\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to impede JavaScript and VBScript to launch executables.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213461","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213461","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213461","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213461r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213461","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000037","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block execution of potentially obfuscated scripts.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\u201d.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Malware and other threats can attempt to obfuscate or hide their malicious code in some script files. This rule prevents scripts that appear to be obfuscated from running. It uses the AntiMalwareScanInterface (AMSI) to determine if a script is potentially obfuscated and then blocks such a script or blocks scripts when an attempt is made to access them.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-92671","V-77975","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"9076","uuid":"db2d19bc-f76b-43da-9963-a72d681864d7","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F04697182F6F38A94BCDCFCBD86A15AFC3AF0371\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block execution of potentially obfuscated scripts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213462","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213462","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213462","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213462r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213462","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000038","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block Win32 imports from macro code in Office.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\". Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This rule blocks potentially malicious behavior by not allowing macro code to execute routines in the Win 32 dynamic link library (DLL).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-92673","V-77977","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"1252","uuid":"e40ceb23-b6ac-4d14-b75a-583f64a1e2c5","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 27D1B20CA9C1DACCE22C33117C8556F14212271E\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block Win32 imports from macro code in Office.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213463","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213463","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213463","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-213463r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213463","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000039","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to prevent user and apps from accessing dangerous websites.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Network Protection >> \"Prevent users and apps from accessing dangerous websites\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Block\" in the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10, it is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Network Protection >> \"Prevent users and apps from accessing dangerous websites\" is set to \"Enabled\u201d and \"Block\" is selected in the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\Network Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableNetworkProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enable Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard network protection to prevent employees from using any application to access dangerous domains that may host phishing scams, exploit-hosting sites, and other malicious content on the internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-92675","V-77979","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"7130","uuid":"e521b5e3-70cb-4b59-9217-4b398bd39443","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B7304616F8F0713A29CFE5A9486DD0739DA964DD\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to prevent user and apps from accessing dangerous websites.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213464","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213464","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213464","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-213464r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-213464","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000040","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level High.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nSelect the \"Show\u2026\" option box and enter \"4\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick the \"Show\u2026\" box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"4\" and the \"Value\" field  contains a \"2\". A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"4\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High  \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-94669","V-79965","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"9709","uuid":"ddb94347-ef13-42ff-a860-7e3e208a3f0f","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 97EF18A97F0A0919500A888A0C1C275AE3E1BDBC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level High.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213465","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213465","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213465","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-213465r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-213465","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000041","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Medium.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\".  \n\nSelect the \"Show\u2026\" option box and enter \"2\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick the \"Show\u2026\" box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"2\" and the \"Value\" field  contains a \"2\". A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"2\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High  \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-94671","V-79967","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"6304","uuid":"b7015487-e769-4ab1-bb8f-e065cc8cb7d8","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CAB2819899EB4B95395B4B2CBDD5A1F7D954CF2E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Medium.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-213466","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213466","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213466","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-213466r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-213466","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000042","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Low.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\".  \n\nSelect the \"Show\u2026\" option box and enter \"1\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\".  \n\nClick the \"Show\u2026\" box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"1\" and the \"Value\" field  contains a \"2\".  A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"1\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-94675","V-79971","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"8606","uuid":"75b11f28-5a53-4d71-86bb-ba406c8e24e7","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-278647","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278647","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278647","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278647r1190726_rule","rule_id":"SV-278647","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000043","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block Adobe Reader from creating child processes.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting prevents Adobe Reader from launching other processes, which can help mitigate security risks associated with malicious PDF files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4256","uuid":"12a14ce3-e266-40d4-9f4d-b98d1f86740e","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ABA718C29A50B77B746BCA3378A3DEE7B7C94811\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must block Adobe Reader from creating child processes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278648","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278648","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278648","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278648r1190728_rule","rule_id":"SV-278648","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000044","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block credential stealing from the Windows local security authority subsystem.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"9e6c4e1f-7d60-472f-ba1a-a39ef669e4b2\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"9e6c4e1f-7d60-472f-ba1a-a39ef669e4b2\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting helps prevent credential stealing by locking down Local Security Authority Subsystem Service (LSASS).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"7559","uuid":"2e9bf31a-4209-4852-b53b-07315efe015b","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D17162F09070E2E79FFA1426B83ED19942F82143\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must block credential stealing from the Windows local security authority subsystem.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278649","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278649","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278649","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278649r1190730_rule","rule_id":"SV-278649","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000045","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block untrusted and unsigned processes that run from USB.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting helps prevents unsigned or untrusted executable files from running from USB removable drives, including SD cards. Blocked file types include executable files (such as .exe, .dll, or .scr).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"5738","uuid":"0970f54c-8b4d-4324-9502-d18a6c17db0e","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 56CE321D750553069DF4B22680FDF4B91E972352\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must block untrusted and unsigned processes that run from USB.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278650","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278650","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278650","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278650r1190732_rule","rule_id":"SV-278650","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000046","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must use advanced protection against ransomware.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting provides an extra layer of protection against ransomware. It uses both client and cloud heuristics to determine whether a file resembles ransomware. This rule does not block files that have one or more of the following characteristics:\n\n- The file is found to be unharmful in the Microsoft cloud.\n- The file is a valid signed file.\n- The file is prevalent enough to not be considered as ransomware.\n- The rule tends to err on the side of caution to prevent ransomware.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"5728","uuid":"05a9e0e8-9e0b-41a2-a9a1-114e48761086","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8EFCB00E70284D0BE416E7BCC2F872E2FADC811D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must use advanced protection against ransomware.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278651","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278651","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278651","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278651r1190734_rule","rule_id":"SV-278651","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000047","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must audit process creations originating from PSExec and WMI commands.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"d1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"2\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"d1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c\" is REG_SZ = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting blocks processes created through PsExec and WMI from running. Both PsExec and WMI can remotely execute code. There is a risk of malware abusing functionality of PsExec and WMI for command and control purposes, or to spread an infection throughout an organization's network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"7899","uuid":"69d85c03-cfb5-427e-b76f-3cea763952d7","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 55C7DC241BAB17CC197845F89513707503A2DBEF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must audit process creations originating from PSExec and WMI commands.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278652","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278652","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278652","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278652r1190736_rule","rule_id":"SV-278652","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000048","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must audit persistence through WMI event subscription.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"e6db77e5-3df2-4cf1-b95a-636979351e5b\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"2\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"e6db77e5-3df2-4cf1-b95a-636979351e5b\" is REG_SZ = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting prevents malware from abusing WMI to attain persistence on a device.\n\nFileless threats employ various tactics to stay hidden, to avoid being seen in the file system, and to gain periodic execution control. Some threats can abuse the WMI repository and event model to stay hidden.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4739","uuid":"bbd2849f-c2e7-4600-86db-b6ddfa8d00a1","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9C81610661328389B392F698BE229F036A4C9925\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must audit persistence through WMI event subscription.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278653","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278653","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278653","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278653r1190738_rule","rule_id":"SV-278653","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000049","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must audit executable files from running unless they meet a prevalence, age, or trusted list criterion.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"2\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25\" is REG_SZ = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting blocks executable files, such as .exe, .dll, or .scr, from launching. Thus, launching untrusted or unknown executable files can be risky, as it might not be initially clear if the files are malicious.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"8272","uuid":"383f0a40-2d61-45ed-9c67-3babb1c655c2","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-278654","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278654","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278654","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278654r1190740_rule","rule_id":"SV-278654","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000050","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block Office communication application from creating child processes.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting prevents Outlook from creating child processes while still allowing legitimate Outlook functions. This rule protects against social engineering attacks and prevents exploiting code from abusing vulnerabilities in Outlook. It also protects against Outlook rules and forms exploits that attackers can use when a user's credentials are compromised.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"6400","uuid":"72080187-45af-478b-aa7f-68a32ec05502","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A784D6ADBAD213B4363CAD8C9763F3D653531BBC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must block Office communication application from creating child processes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278655","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278655","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278655","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278655r1190742_rule","rule_id":"SV-278655","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000051","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block abuse of exploited vulnerable signed drivers.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting prevents an application from writing a vulnerable signed driver to disk. Vulnerable signed drivers can be exploited by local applications that have sufficient privileges to gain access to the kernel. Vulnerable signed drivers enable attackers to disable or circumvent security solutions, eventually leading to system compromise.\n\nThe Block abuse of exploited vulnerable signed drivers rule does not block a driver already existing on the system from being loaded.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"6409","uuid":"88f0e6d1-615d-46de-8cdd-80c527f21246","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C7E2B1D6D5800CC4B46D8B0A6B98C96E41F7C2FF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must block abuse of exploited vulnerable signed drivers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278656","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278656","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278656","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278656r1190744_rule","rule_id":"SV-278656","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000052","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must configure local administrator merge behavior for lists.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Configure local administrator merge behavior for lists to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Configure local administrator merge behavior for lists is set to \"Enabled\". Otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableLocalAdminMerge\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures how locally defined lists are combined or merged with globally defined lists. This setting applies to exclusion lists, specified remediation lists, and attack surface reduction.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"7977","uuid":"94b3c6da-4806-40a4-9426-1c0f7bb481b9","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 36A956C88CF351DDB6ADC16F625527894A83BF0C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must configure local administrator merge behavior for lists.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278658","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278658","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278658","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278658r1190746_rule","rule_id":"SV-278658","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000054","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must control whether exclusions are visible to Local Admins.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Control whether exclusions are visible to Local Admins to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Control whether or not exclusions are visible to Local Admins is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"HideExclusionsFromLocalAdmins\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is \"0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabled (Default): If this setting is not configured or disabled, local admins can see exclusions in the Windows Security App or via PowerShell.\n\nEnabled: If this setting is enabled, local admins no longer see the exclusion list in Windows Security App or via PowerShell.O13.\n\nNote: Applying this setting will not remove exclusions, it only prevents them from being visible to local admins. This is reflected in?Get-MpPreference.I13.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"6564","uuid":"9b36de58-9137-4618-b9f3-e2201fb0b29a","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 63D87BC1B0B9A4BA5237BD84BD0BC0A1A625089F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must control whether exclusions are visible to Local Admins.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278659","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278659","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278659","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-278659r1190748_rule","rule_id":"SV-278659","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000055","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must randomize scheduled task times.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Randomize scheduled task times to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Randomize scheduled task times is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"RandomizeScheduleTaskTimes\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In Microsoft Defender Antivirus, randomize the start time of the scan to any interval from 0 to 23 hours. By default, scheduled tasks begin at a random time within four hours of the time specified in Task Scheduler.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3763","uuid":"3a5805cf-d97f-4ebd-9f6e-ba032827a7aa","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AAE14A31F9811C902C777A99CD356E83EDEC209A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must randomize scheduled task times.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278660","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278660","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278660","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278660r1190750_rule","rule_id":"SV-278660","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000056","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must hide the Family options area.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Security >> Family Options >> Hide the Family options area to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Security >> Family Options >> Hide the Family options area is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender Security Center\\Family options\n\nCriteria: If the value \"UILockdown\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Family options section contains links to settings and further information for parents of a Windows PC. It is not intended for enterprise or business environments.\n\nThis section can be hidden from users of the machine. This option can be useful if you do not want users in the organization to see or have access to this section.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"5040","uuid":"7c0f3fc3-a0c3-4cf7-b6c3-bf9b8d867db5","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 96060703DF7F05A02E7241EA591B7FFEAB7D3A20\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must hide the Family options area.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278661","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278661","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278661","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278661r1190752_rule","rule_id":"SV-278661","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000057","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable the file hash computation feature.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MpEngine >>Enable file hash computation feature to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MpEngine >> Enable file hash computation feature is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableFileHashComputation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy drives the ability to enforce Indicators of Compromise (IoC) by using file hash allow/block indicators.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"1995","uuid":"86b2f2b3-7b01-422f-8793-6f514f4b50cf","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A288F20BA449DF59C3A4BA4E40E4C4BC7CAC8A2B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must enable the file hash computation feature.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278662","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278662","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278662","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278662r1190754_rule","rule_id":"SV-278662","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000058","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable extended cloud check.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MpEngine >> Configure extended cloud check to \"Enabled\" with a Policy Option value of \"50\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MpEngine >> Configure extended cloud check is set to \"Enabled\" with a Policy Option value of \"50\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\n\nCriteria: If the value \"MpBafsExtendedTimeout\" is REG_DWORD = 50, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 50, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When Microsoft Defender Antivirus finds a suspicious file, it can prevent the file from running while it queries the Microsoft Defender Antivirus cloud service.\n\nThe default period that the file is blocked is 10 seconds. Extending the cloud block timeout period can help ensure there is enough time to receive a proper determination from the Microsoft Defender Antivirus cloud service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"5473","uuid":"fc76eab8-cf28-436c-8e62-3d1194d6ac1a","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-278668","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278668","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278668","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-278668r1190756_rule","rule_id":"SV-278668","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000064","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable script scanning.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> Turn on script scanning to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> Turn on script scanning is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableScriptScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Always-on protection consists of real-time protection, behavior monitoring, and heuristics to identify malware based on known suspicious and malicious activities. These activities include events, such as processes making unusual changes to existing files, modifying or creating automatic startup registry keys and startup locations (also known as autostart extensibility points, or ASEPs), and other changes to the file system or file structure.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3797","uuid":"acda9fad-6bae-427f-b2e8-966c14515290","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ACF54503D1C9AC1C86ED7DCBC90800E0F3A55CAA\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Microsoft Defender AV must enable script scanning.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278669","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278669","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278669","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-278669r1190758_rule","rule_id":"SV-278669","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000065","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> Configure real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> Configure real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"OobeEnableRtpAndSigUpdate\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Always-on protection consists of real-time protection, behavior monitoring, and heuristics to identify malware based on known suspicious and malicious activities. These activities include events, such as processes making unusual changes to existing files, modifying or creating automatic startup registry keys and startup locations (also known as autostart extensibility points, or ASEPs), and other changes to the file system or file structure.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"6712","uuid":"4c1da23f-0c72-4823-9b4b-ec154a0929a4","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 62E472B60DD6EE35A869BA3ADE34B0D44E4DBAC5\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Microsoft Defender AV must enable real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278672","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278672","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278672","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278672r1190761_rule","rule_id":"SV-278672","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000068","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable network protection to be configured into block or audit mode on Windows Server.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Network Protection >> This settings controls whether Network Protection is allowed to be configured into block or audit mode on Windows Server to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: This requirement is not applicable to desktops.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Network Protection >> This settings controls whether Network Protection is allowed to be configured into block or audit mode on Windows Server is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\Network Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"AllowNetworkProtectionOnWinServer\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft's Exploit Guard comprises several techniques to defend against phishing attacks and malware. These include controlled folder access, attack surface reduction, and network protection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"8187","uuid":"62807e38-6ed1-4557-9dfd-32f79ef0a932","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 68EE38C3641523BCAE5AAB9D7F78CFCFE1777EFA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must enable network protection to be configured into block or audit mode on Windows Server.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278674","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278674","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278674","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278674r1190763_rule","rule_id":"SV-278674","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000070","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable EDR in block mode.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Features >> Enable EDR in block mode to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Features >> Enable EDR in block mode is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Features\n\nCriteria: If the value \"PassiveRemediation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"EDR in block mode allows Microsoft Defender Antivirus to take actions on post-breach, behavioral EDR detections. EDR in block mode is integrated with threat and vulnerability management capabilities.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"8935","uuid":"23c755ec-ce28-4e4b-97e7-cd38b5a2249c","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4D7934965390A11F64F0D95C225E8C176FE76C92\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must enable EDR in block mode.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278675","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278675","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278675","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278675r1190765_rule","rule_id":"SV-278675","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000071","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must report Dynamic Signature dropped events.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Reporting >> Configure whether to report Dynamic Signature dropped events to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Reporting >> Configure whether to report Dynamic Signature dropped events is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Reporting\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableDynamicSignatureDroppedEventReporting\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft Defender Antivirus logs \"Dynamic Signature dropped\" events when it blocks or removes a file based on a dynamically updated signature, but the signature itself is dropped, meaning it was not fully processed or applied. This can indicate a potential issue with signature updates or the system's ability to handle them.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"8136","uuid":"c1311b44-4d06-4e23-833f-755a1d5a054d","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1815DF0A950A1CFB5B48558D741623C4439D593D\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Microsoft Defender AV must report Dynamic Signature dropped events.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278676","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278676","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278676","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-278676r1190767_rule","rule_id":"SV-278676","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000072","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must scan excluded files and directories during quick scans.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> Scan excluded files and directories during quick scans to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> Scan excluded files and directories during quick scans is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"QuickScanIncludeExclusions\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In Microsoft Defender Antivirus, when an exclusion for a file or folder is created, it will generally be skipped during both real-time protection and on-demand scans (including quick scans and full scans). However, with newer releases, the option exists to configure quick scans to include files and directories that are otherwise excluded from real-time protection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3340","uuid":"92dfde0c-3e86-4978-bfd4-320ac938bffe","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FC89FA75AD5ED75B5FF4AAFA2BFB59262A7924DB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must scan excluded files and directories during quick scans.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278677","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278677","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278677","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278677r1190769_rule","rule_id":"SV-278677","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000074","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must convert warn verdict to block.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Network Inspection System >> Convert warn verdict to block to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Network Inspection System >> Convert warn verdict to block is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableConvertWarnToBlock\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If a site URL has an unknown or uncertain reputation, a toast notification presents the user with the following options:\n\n- Ok: The toast notification is released (removed), and the attempt to access the site is ended.\n\n- Unblock: The user has access to the site for 24 hours, at which point the block is reenabled. The user can continue to use Unblock to access the site until such time that the administrator prohibits (blocks) the site, thus removing the option to Unblock.\n\n- Feedback: The toast notification presents the user with a link to submit a ticket, which the user can use to submit feedback to the administrator in an attempt to justify access to the site.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"9673","uuid":"9f1711f8-df61-4f06-81e8-254d18379dc1","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8B3A1920DA59329EB924A8D730264126EA29286E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must convert warn verdict to block.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278678","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278678","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278678","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278678r1190771_rule","rule_id":"SV-278678","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000075","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable asynchronous inspection.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Network Inspection System >> Turn on asynchronous inspection to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Network Inspection System >> Turn on asynchronous inspection is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\n\nCriteria: If the value \"AllowSwitchToAsyncInspection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Network protection includes performance optimization that allows block mode to asynchronously inspect long-lived connections, which might provide a performance improvement. This optimization can also help with app compatibility problems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"2809","uuid":"5860d373-f2eb-4126-9c20-78f0173e64ef","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A48BD0DE1B1872BEE3E068301C0FE28EB4C8ADEE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must enable asynchronous inspection.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278679","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278679","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278679","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-278679r1190773_rule","rule_id":"SV-278679","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000076","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must scan packed executables.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> Scan packed executables to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> Scan packed executables is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisablePackedExeScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting manages whether Microsoft Defender Antivirus scans packed executables. Packed executables are executable files that contain compressed code.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"5844","uuid":"5d902dc3-1fa8-443f-8aba-01adba028b1c","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F8FF40D5F8E2C33E95A1D5CA6E23AB390633513F\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Microsoft Defender AV must scan packed executables.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278680","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278680","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278680","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-278680r1190775_rule","rule_id":"SV-278680","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000077","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable heuristics.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> Turn on heuristics to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> Turn on heuristics is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableHeuristics\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Always-on protection consists of real-time protection, behavior monitoring, and heuristics to identify malware based on known suspicious and malicious activities.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"9343","uuid":"c25e7d90-fe8b-49d9-a546-e794bd3799f2","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 568F33CE9D50CB3D29BF8F5E8E8A61F58D3C73D0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must enable heuristics.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."},{"group_id_src":"V-278863","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278863","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278863","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-278863r1190777_rule","rule_id":"SV-278863","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000073","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must set cloud protection level to High.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MpEngine >> Select cloud protection level to \"Enabled\".\n\nSet policy value \"Select cloud blocking level\" to \"High blocking level\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MpEngine >> Select cloud protection level is set to \"Enabled\". Verify the policy value for \"Select cloud blocking level\" is set to \"High blocking level\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\n\nCriteria: If the value \"MpCloudBlockLevel\" is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Cloud protection in Microsoft Defender Antivirus delivers accurate, real-time, and intelligent protection. Cloud protection should be enabled by default.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"6973","uuid":"fc095838-3928-4e28-9a9a-3b61752bf408","stig_uuid":"e6e831fd-e57c-4f91-a3ad-528e3dde0994","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderAV_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F579B32054D039A54B690EC16C809BCE8303487F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Microsoft Defender AV must set cloud protection level to High.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Defender Antivirus."}]},{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-23T17:12:42.0000000+00:00","module":{"name":"Scan-DefenderFirewall_Checks","version":"1.2604.2"}},"stig_name":"Microsoft Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Microsoft Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security","stig_id":"Windows_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security","release_info":"Release: 2 Benchmark Date: 09 Nov 2023","version":"2","uuid":"b337daff-f591-46da-aaf2-546eec56e200","reference_identifier":"5552","size":21,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-241989","group_tree":[{"id":"V-241989","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-241989","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-241989r922928_rule","rule_id":"SV-241989","rule_version":"WNFWA-000001","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must be enabled when connected to a domain.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Domain Profile tab >> State, \"Firewall state\" to \"On (recommended)\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set domainprofile state on\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles state on\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, the Domain Profile requirements can be marked NA.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\DomainProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableFirewall\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\DomainProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableFirewall\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. This setting enables the firewall when connected to the domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-17415","SV-54833","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"3907","uuid":"f2465cac-9187-4d64-9f28-8e9b5e63ca1f","stig_uuid":"b337daff-f591-46da-aaf2-546eec56e200","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderFirewall_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9CC8EBCACB07A16CAB573BED9E0CC5971AB4552F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must be enabled when connected to a domain.' matches the expected value on Windows Defender Firewall."},{"group_id_src":"V-241990","group_tree":[{"id":"V-241990","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-241990","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-241990r922930_rule","rule_id":"SV-241990","rule_version":"WNFWA-000002","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must be enabled when connected to a private network.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Private Profile tab >> State, \"Firewall state\" to \"On (recommended)\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set privateprofile state on\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles state on\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PrivateProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableFirewall\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\StandardProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableFirewall\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. This setting enables the firewall when connected to a private network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-17416","SV-54849","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"6643","uuid":"9431315a-37d2-4f67-96c3-ca18a1048e64","stig_uuid":"b337daff-f591-46da-aaf2-546eec56e200","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderFirewall_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 01F22C280A24B70C6601F8E6453D0607F66ECA93\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must be enabled when connected to a private network.' matches the expected value on Windows Defender Firewall."},{"group_id_src":"V-241991","group_tree":[{"id":"V-241991","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-241991","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-241991r922932_rule","rule_id":"SV-241991","rule_version":"WNFWA-000003","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must be enabled when connected to a public network.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Public Profile tab >> State, \"Firewall state\" to \"On (recommended)\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set publicprofile state on\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles state on\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableFirewall\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\PublicProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableFirewall\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. This setting enables the firewall when connected to a public network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-17417","SV-54855","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"9099","uuid":"ef75a30b-3478-4013-8019-dd12be53da7d","stig_uuid":"b337daff-f591-46da-aaf2-546eec56e200","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderFirewall_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4F7EFACB84A29CF1634E220C1091CC39E3CBB90A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must be enabled when connected to a public network.' matches the expected value on Windows Defender Firewall."},{"group_id_src":"V-241992","group_tree":[{"id":"V-241992","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-241992","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-241992r922934_rule","rule_id":"SV-241992","rule_version":"WNFWA-000004","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must block unsolicited inbound connections when connected to a domain.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Domain Profile tab >> State, \"Inbound connections\" to \"Block (default)\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set domainprofile firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound\".\n\nBoth inbound and outbound parameters must be specified to execute this command.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, the Domain Profile requirements can be marked NA.\n\nIf the system is a member of a domain and the firewall's Domain Profile is not enabled (see V-17415), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\DomainProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultInboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\DomainProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultInboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Unsolicited inbound connections may be malicious attempts to gain access to a system. Unsolicited inbound connections, for which there is no rule allowing the connection, will be blocked in the domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-17418","SV-54859","CCI-000382"],"reference_identifier":"8755","uuid":"17d83de0-8deb-4770-9b21-94ad3dbc2fe3","stig_uuid":"b337daff-f591-46da-aaf2-546eec56e200","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3FF989CEC01149C1188AA770AA65C317D37BB7E8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must block unsolicited inbound connections when connected to a domain.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Windows Defender Firewall."},{"group_id_src":"V-241993","group_tree":[{"id":"V-241993","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-241993","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-241993r922936_rule","rule_id":"SV-241993","rule_version":"WNFWA-000005","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must allow outbound connections, unless a rule explicitly blocks the connection when connected to a domain.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Domain Profile tab >> State, \"Outbound connections\" to \"Allow (default)\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set domainprofile firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound\".\n\nBoth inbound and outbound parameters must be specified to execute this command.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, the Domain Profile requirements can be marked NA.\n\nIf the system is a member of a domain and the firewall's Domain Profile is not enabled (see V-17415), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\DomainProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultOutboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\DomainProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultOutboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Outbound connections are allowed in the domain, unless a rule explicitly blocks the connection. This allows normal outbound communication, which could be restricted as necessary with additional rules.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-17419","SV-54863","CCI-001094"],"reference_identifier":"5874","uuid":"255391ff-db0b-4b5c-bd89-9ea00baf27ad","stig_uuid":"b337daff-f591-46da-aaf2-546eec56e200","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2E32530E2554603B8E93701EBC782CE013F7E957\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must allow outbound connections, unless a rule explicitly blocks the connection when connected to a domain.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Windows Defender Firewall."},{"group_id_src":"V-241994","group_tree":[{"id":"V-241994","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-241994","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-241994r922938_rule","rule_id":"SV-241994","rule_version":"WNFWA-000009","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security log size must be configured for domain connections.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Domain Profile tab >> Logging (select Customize), \"Size limit (KB):\" to \"16,384\" or greater.\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh command may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set domainprofile logging maxfilesize 16384\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, the Domain Profile requirements can be marked NA.\n\nIf the system is a member of a domain and the firewall's Domain Profile is not enabled (see V-17415), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\DomainProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogFileSize\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00004000 (16384) (or greater)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\DomainProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogFileSize\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00004000 (16384) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. The firewall log file size for a domain connection will be set to ensure enough capacity is allocated for audit data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-17425","SV-54874","CCI-000140"],"reference_identifier":"4411","uuid":"3b94521b-f56b-4e9d-b7ff-f776aa8a66f1","stig_uuid":"b337daff-f591-46da-aaf2-546eec56e200","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderFirewall_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7FAE742E95D852CFFAE8D0636C480A97B8DD69A9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security log size must be configured for domain connections.' matches the expected value on Windows Defender Firewall."},{"group_id_src":"V-241995","group_tree":[{"id":"V-241995","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-241995","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-241995r922940_rule","rule_id":"SV-241995","rule_version":"WNFWA-000010","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must log dropped packets when connected to a domain.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Domain Profile tab >> Logging (select Customize), \"Log dropped packets\" to \"Yes\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set domainprofile logging droppedconnections enable\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles logging droppedconnections enable\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, the Domain Profile requirements can be marked NA.\n\nIf the system is a member of a domain and the firewall's Domain Profile is not enabled (see V-17415), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\DomainProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogDroppedPackets\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\DomainProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogDroppedPackets\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Logging of dropped packets for a domain connection will be enabled to maintain an audit trail of potential issues.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-17426","SV-54877","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"9412","uuid":"bb3fee0b-8444-4760-8710-43462dbae442","stig_uuid":"b337daff-f591-46da-aaf2-546eec56e200","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B8801C126069070EF553EC95681240473320AF6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must log dropped packets when connected to a domain.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Windows Defender Firewall."},{"group_id_src":"V-241996","group_tree":[{"id":"V-241996","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-241996","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-241996r922942_rule","rule_id":"SV-241996","rule_version":"WNFWA-000011","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must log successful connections when connected to a domain.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Domain Profile tab >> Logging (select Customize), \"Log successful connections\" to \"Yes\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set domainprofile logging allowedconnections enable\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles logging allowedconnections enable\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, the Domain Profile requirements can be marked NA.\n\nIf the system is a member of a domain and the firewall's Domain Profile is not enabled (see V-17415), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\DomainProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogSuccessfulConnections\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\DomainProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogSuccessfulConnections\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Logging of successful connections for a domain connection will be enabled to maintain an audit trail if issues are discovered.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-17427","SV-54878","CCI-001462"],"reference_identifier":"8897","uuid":"ec4d95e6-5058-4f84-afe1-4119c5b49e35","stig_uuid":"b337daff-f591-46da-aaf2-546eec56e200","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-DefenderFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CA1C34CB438BF0B9D926A21540F0A035E3974236\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must log successful connections when connected to a domain.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Windows Defender Firewall."},{"group_id_src":"V-241997","group_tree":[{"id":"V-241997","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-241997","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-241997r922944_rule","rule_id":"SV-241997","rule_version":"WNFWA-000012","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must block unsolicited inbound connections when connected to a private network.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Private Profile tab >> State, \"Inbound connections\" to \"Block (default)\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set privateprofile firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound\".\n\nBoth inbound and outbound parameters must be specified to execute this command.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the firewall's Private Profile is not enabled (see V-17416), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PrivateProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultInboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\StandardProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultInboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Unsolicited inbound connections may be malicious attempts to gain access to a system. Unsolicited inbound connections, for which there is no rule allowing the connection, will be blocked on a private network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-17428","SV-54879","CCI-000382"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"3b377169-658f-4f77-a292-37e355b6eece","stig_uuid":"b337daff-f591-46da-aaf2-546eec56e200","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-241998","group_tree":[{"id":"V-241998","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-241998","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-241998r922946_rule","rule_id":"SV-241998","rule_version":"WNFWA-000013","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must allow outbound connections, unless a rule explicitly blocks the connection when connected to a private network.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Private Profile tab >> State, \"Outbound connections\" to \"Allow (default)\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set privateprofile firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound\".\n\nBoth inbound and outbound parameters must be specified to execute this command.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the firewall's Private Profile is not enabled (see V-17416), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PrivateProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultOutboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\StandardProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultOutboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Outbound connections are allowed on a private network, unless a rule explicitly blocks the connection. This allows normal outbound communication, which could be restricted as necessary with additional rules.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-17429","SV-54890","CCI-001094"],"reference_ide